{"term": "1996", "caseName": "United States v. O'Hagan", "caseLink": "https://www.oyez.org/cases/1996/96-842", "caseTranscripts": [{"transcriptTitle": "Oral Argument - April 16, 1997", "transcriptLink": "https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/rehnquist10/oral_argument_audio/21006", "transcript": [{"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "We'll hear argument now in Number 96-842, United States v. James Herman O'Hagan.", "start": 0, "stop": 8.748, "duration": 8.75, "cleanText": [["we", "will", "hear", "argument", "now", "in", "number", "united", "state", "v", "james", "herman", "ohagan"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Dreeben.", "start": 8.748, "stop": 9.857, "duration": 1.11, "cleanText": [["mr", "dreeben"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice, and may it please the Court:", "start": 9.857, "stop": 12.77, "duration": 2.91, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "and", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "Information is the lifeblood of the securities markets.", "start": 12.77, "stop": 17.003, "duration": 4.23, "cleanText": [["information", "be", "the", "lifeblood", "of", "the", "security", "market"]]}, {"text": "Markets thrive on legitimate efforts to acquire, analyze, and use information, but the deceptive acquisition and use of information in securities trading serves no legitimate purpose.", "start": 17.003, "stop": 30.881, "duration": 13.88, "cleanText": [["market", "thrive", "on", "legitimate", "effort", "to", "acquire", "analyze", "and", "use", "information", "but", "the", "deceptive", "acquisition", "and", "use", "of", "information", "in", "security", "trade", "serve", "no", "legitimate", "purpose"]]}, {"text": "Respondent's securities trading involved just such deception.", "start": 30.881, "stop": 35.195, "duration": 4.31, "cleanText": [["respondent", "s", "security", "trading", "involve", "just", "such", "deception"]]}, {"text": "Respondent is a lawyer whose firm was entrusted with the confidential plans of a client that had planned to make a tender offer for the Pillsbury company.", "start": 35.195, "stop": 46.632, "duration": 11.44, "cleanText": [["respondent", "be", "a", "lawyer", "whose", "firm", "be", "entrust", "with", "the", "confidential", "plan", "of", "a", "client", "that", "have", "plan", "to", "make", "a", "tender", "offer", "for", "the", "pillsbury", "company"]]}, {"text": "While posing as a loyal partner in his law firm, respondent misappropriated that information in breach of his fiduciary duties to the firm and his client and reaped personal profits in virtually risk-free trading in Pillsbury stock and options.", "start": 46.632, "stop": 63.633, "duration": 17, "cleanText": [["while", "pose", "as", "a", "loyal", "partner", "in", "his", "law", "firm", "respondent", "misappropriate", "that", "information", "in", "breach", "of", "his", "fiduciary", "duty", "to", "the", "firm", "and", "his", "client", "and", "reap", "personal", "profit", "in", "virtually", "risk", "free", "trading", "in", "pillsbury", "stock", "and", "option"]]}, {"text": "By engaging in that form of deception in connection with his trading, respondent violated three prohibitions of Federal law: section 10(b) of the Securities Exchange Act, section 14(e) of the Exchange Act, and the mail fraud statute.", "start": 63.633, "stop": 81.625, "duration": 17.99, "cleanText": [["by", "engage", "in", "that", "form", "of", "deception", "in", "connection", "with", "his", "trading", "respondent", "violate", "three", "prohibition", "of", "federal", "law", "section", "b", "of", "the", "security", "exchange", "act", "section", "e", "of", "the", "exchange", "act", "and", "the", "mail", "fraud", "statute"]]}, {"text": "Now, the misappropriation theory under section 10(b) of the Securities Exchange Act posits that a fiduciary or other person with a similar relationship of trust and confidence commits deception on the legitimate owner of information if that fiduciary or other agent misappropriates the information by using it in securities trading, contrary to the view of the United States Court of Appeals for the Eighth Circuit.", "start": 81.625, "stop": 110.774, "duration": 29.15, "cleanText": [["now", "the", "misappropriation", "theory", "under", "section", "b", "of", "the", "security", "exchange", "act", "posit", "that", "a", "fiduciary", "or", "other", "person", "with", "a", "similar", "relationship", "of", "trust", "and", "confidence", "commits", "deception", "on", "the", "legitimate", "owner", "of", "information", "if", "that", "fiduciary", "or", "other", "agent", "misappropriate", "the", "information", "by", "use", "it", "in", "security", "trading", "contrary", "to", "the", "view", "of", "the", "united", "state", "court", "of", "appeal", "for", "the", "eighth", "circuit"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Dreeben, just by misappropriating?", "start": 110.774, "stop": 113.474, "duration": 2.7, "cleanText": [["mr", "dreeben", "just", "by", "misappropriate"]]}, {"text": "I mean, suppose the defendant here had instead come clean, and he told his superiors in the law firm that he was going to use this information.", "start": 113.474, "stop": 127.704, "duration": 14.23, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "suppose", "the", "defendant", "here", "have", "instead", "come", "clean", "and", "he", "tell", "his", "superior", "in", "the", "law", "firm", "that", "he", "be", "go", "to", "use", "this", "information"]]}, {"text": "Then he would not be posing as a loyal employee any more, and it would have been okay.", "start": 127.704, "stop": 132.809, "duration": 5.11, "cleanText": [["then", "he", "would", "not", "be", "pose", "as", "a", "loyal", "employee", "any", "more", "and", "it", "would", "have", "be", "okay"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "He would not have deceived his employer.", "start": 132.809, "stop": 135.181, "duration": 2.37, "cleanText": [["he", "would", "not", "have", "deceive", "his", "employer"]]}, {"text": "He still would have breached independent fiduciary duties that he owed to that employer.", "start": 135.181, "stop": 140.043, "duration": 4.86, "cleanText": [["he", "still", "would", "have", "breach", "independent", "fiduciary", "duty", "that", "he", "owe", "to", "that", "employer"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "And you say he would still have breached the securities laws.", "start": 140.043, "stop": 143.315, "duration": 3.27, "cleanText": [["and", "you", "say", "he", "would", "still", "have", "breach", "the", "security", "law"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, I do not think he would have breached the securities laws.", "start": 143.315, "stop": 145.906, "duration": 2.59, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "do", "not", "think", "he", "would", "have", "breach", "the", "security", "law"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "So that's the line.", "start": 145.906, "stop": 146.247, "duration": 0.34, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "be", "the", "line"]]}, {"text": "He didn't tell them that he was going to go out and use it.", "start": 146.247, "stop": 148.517, "duration": 2.27, "cleanText": [["he", "do", "not", "tell", "them", "that", "he", "be", "go", "to", "go", "out", "and", "use", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's absolutely correct, and the reason why that is significant is that section 10(b) prohibits deceptive devices and contrivances.", "start": 148.517, "stop": 156.963, "duration": 8.45, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "absolutely", "correct", "and", "the", "reason", "why", "that", "be", "significant", "be", "that", "section", "b", "prohibit", "deceptive", "device", "and", "contrivance"]]}, {"text": "It requires deception.", "start": 156.963, "stop": 158.635, "duration": 1.67, "cleanText": [["it", "require", "deception"]]}, {"text": "The misappropriation theory does involve a breach of fiduciary duty, but the distinctive factor about that breach is that it is a deceptive breach.", "start": 158.635, "stop": 168.44, "duration": 9.81, "cleanText": [["the", "misappropriation", "theory", "do", "involve", "a", "breach", "of", "fiduciary", "duty", "but", "the", "distinctive", "factor", "about", "that", "breach", "be", "that", "it", "be", "a", "deceptive", "breach"]]}, {"text": "It involves, just as the facts did in Carpenter v. United States, an agent entrusted with information by a principal under the understanding between the parties that the agent would not use that information for any personal gain without obtaining the principal's agreement.", "start": 168.44, "stop": 190.545, "duration": 22.1, "cleanText": [["it", "involve", "just", "as", "the", "fact", "do", "in", "carpenter", "v", "united", "state", "an", "agent", "entrust", "with", "information", "by", "a", "principal", "under", "the", "understanding", "between", "the", "party", "that", "the", "agent", "would", "not", "use", "that", "information", "for", "any", "personal", "gain", "without", "obtain", "the", "principal", "s", "agreement"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, Mr. Dreeben, then if someone stole the lawyer's briefcase and discovered the information and traded on it, no violation?", "start": 190.545, "stop": 202.073, "duration": 11.53, "cleanText": [["well", "mr", "dreeben", "then", "if", "someone", "steal", "the", "lawyer", "s", "briefcase", "and", "discover", "the", "information", "and", "trade", "on", "it", "no", "violation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct, Justice O'Connor.", "start": 202.073, "stop": 203.645, "duration": 1.57, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "justice", "oconnor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "And if a partner perhaps in the law firm, the lawyer let his daughter know about the planned merger inadvertently and the daughter relied on the information and bought stock options, violation?", "start": 203.645, "stop": 226.789, "duration": 23.14, "cleanText": [["and", "if", "a", "partner", "perhaps", "in", "the", "law", "firm", "the", "lawyer", "let", "his", "daughter", "know", "about", "the", "planned", "merger", "inadvertently", "and", "the", "daughter", "rely", "on", "the", "information", "and", "buy", "stock", "option", "violation"]]}, {"text": "The daughter has no obligation to disclose.", "start": 226.789, "stop": 229.992, "duration": 3.2, "cleanText": [["the", "daughter", "have", "no", "obligation", "to", "disclose"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Correct, Justice O'Connor, and the answer to that is probably not, although there has been litigation about whether in particular circumstances a family relationship is sufficiently imbued with a business context that there is a duty that runs to it, but I accept the general thrust of your hypotheticals.", "start": 229.992, "stop": 250.045, "duration": 20.05, "cleanText": [["correct", "justice", "oconnor", "and", "the", "answer", "to", "that", "be", "probably", "not", "although", "there", "have", "be", "litigation", "about", "whether", "in", "particular", "circumstance", "a", "family", "relationship", "be", "sufficiently", "imbue", "with", "a", "business", "context", "that", "there", "be", "a", "duty", "that", "run", "to", "it", "but", "i", "accept", "the", "general", "thrust", "of", "your", "hypothetical"]]}, {"text": "There are forms of improper conduct that section 10(b) does not reach, and the reason why section 10(b) does not reach them is it is a statute that is framed to reach fraudulent deceptive activity in connection with securities trading.", "start": 250.045, "stop": 265.496, "duration": 15.45, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "form", "of", "improper", "conduct", "that", "section", "b", "do", "not", "reach", "and", "the", "reason", "why", "section", "b", "do", "not", "reach", "them", "be", "it", "be", "a", "statute", "that", "be", "frame", "to", "reach", "fraudulent", "deceptive", "activity", "in", "connection", "with", "security", "trading"]]}, {"text": "That is--", "start": 265.496, "stop": 266.675, "duration": 1.18, "cleanText": [["that", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, Mr. Dreeben, where is... the thing that bothers me about the case here is, where is the connection between the deceptive device and the purchase or sale of a security?", "start": 266.675, "stop": 280.603, "duration": 13.93, "cleanText": [["well", "mr", "dreeben", "where", "be", "the", "thing", "that", "bother", "me", "about", "the", "case", "here", "be", "where", "be", "the", "connection", "between", "the", "deceptive", "device", "and", "the", "purchase", "or", "sale", "of", "a", "security"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The connection, Chief Justice Rehnquist, lies in the fact that the misappropriation does not occur until the lawyer uses the information as the basis for his trades.", "start": 280.603, "stop": 292.173, "duration": 11.57, "cleanText": [["the", "connection", "chief", "justice", "rehnquist", "lie", "in", "the", "fact", "that", "the", "misappropriation", "do", "not", "occur", "until", "the", "lawyer", "use", "the", "information", "as", "the", "basis", "for", "his", "trade"]]}, {"text": "It is that very information which drives his participation in the market and allows the profits to be reached... reaped by him.", "start": 292.173, "stop": 302.109, "duration": 9.94, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "that", "very", "information", "which", "drive", "his", "participation", "in", "the", "market", "and", "allow", "the", "profit", "to", "be", "reach", "reap", "by", "him"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "But he didn't deceive anyone who sold him securities.", "start": 302.109, "stop": 306.282, "duration": 4.17, "cleanText": [["but", "he", "do", "not", "deceive", "anyone", "who", "sell", "him", "security"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is true.", "start": 306.282, "stop": 307.15, "duration": 0.87, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "true"]]}, {"text": "The misappropriation theory doesn't rely on the notion that he owed a duty of disclosure to the shareholders on the other side of the transaction, but it does satisfy the requisite connection between the fraud and the securities trading, because it is only in the trading that the fraud is consummated.", "start": 307.15, "stop": 328.736, "duration": 21.59, "cleanText": [["the", "misappropriation", "theory", "do", "not", "rely", "on", "the", "notion", "that", "he", "owe", "a", "duty", "of", "disclosure", "to", "the", "shareholder", "on", "the", "other", "side", "of", "the", "transaction", "but", "it", "do", "satisfy", "the", "requisite", "connection", "between", "the", "fraud", "and", "the", "security", "trading", "because", "it", "be", "only", "in", "the", "trading", "that", "the", "fraud", "be", "consummate"]]}, {"text": "There could be no closer--", "start": 328.736, "stop": 330.108, "duration": 1.37, "cleanText": [["there", "could", "be", "no", "closer"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "But you think of fraud being practiced on a person who is damaged by it.", "start": 330.108, "stop": 335.103, "duration": 5, "cleanText": [["but", "you", "think", "of", "fraud", "be", "practice", "on", "a", "person", "who", "be", "damage", "by", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I think that under the common law view of fraud, Chief Justice Rehnquist, that is an accurate statement, but the securities laws are not framed to pick up only those violations that are covered by common law fraud.", "start": 335.103, "stop": 348.671, "duration": 13.57, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "under", "the", "common", "law", "view", "of", "fraud", "chief", "justice", "rehnquist", "that", "be", "an", "accurate", "statement", "but", "the", "security", "law", "be", "not", "frame", "to", "pick", "up", "only", "those", "violation", "that", "be", "cover", "by", "common", "law", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "Congress did not pass a statute that says, it is unlawful to commit fraud on the purchaser or seller of securities.", "start": 348.671, "stop": 356.705, "duration": 8.03, "cleanText": [["congress", "do", "not", "pass", "a", "statute", "that", "say", "it", "be", "unlawful", "to", "commit", "fraud", "on", "the", "purchaser", "or", "seller", "of", "security"]]}, {"text": "Congress did not pass a law even that said it is unlawful to commit fraud in a securities transaction.", "start": 356.705, "stop": 363.25, "duration": 6.55, "cleanText": [["congress", "do", "not", "pass", "a", "law", "even", "that", "say", "it", "be", "unlawful", "to", "commit", "fraud", "in", "a", "security", "transaction"]]}, {"text": "It passed a law with a broader phrase, in connection with a securities transaction, because the very aim of this section was to pick up unforeseen, cunning, deceptive devices that people might cleverly use in the securities markets--", "start": 363.25, "stop": 379.552, "duration": 16.3, "cleanText": [["it", "pass", "a", "law", "with", "a", "broad", "phrase", "in", "connection", "with", "a", "security", "transaction", "because", "the", "very", "aim", "of", "this", "section", "be", "to", "pick", "up", "unforeseen", "cunning", "deceptive", "device", "that", "people", "might", "cleverly", "use", "in", "the", "security", "market"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's rather unusual, for a criminal statute to be that open-ended, isn't it?", "start": 379.552, "stop": 383.575, "duration": 4.02, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "rather", "unusual", "for", "a", "criminal", "statute", "to", "be", "that", "open", "end", "be", "not", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I don't think that it's unusual to give the text of this statute its natural reading.", "start": 383.575, "stop": 389.369, "duration": 5.79, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "that", "it", "be", "unusual", "to", "give", "the", "text", "of", "this", "statute", "its", "natural", "reading"]]}, {"text": "What it requires is proof of fraud, and then it requires proof that there's a connection between the fraud and the trading.", "start": 389.369, "stop": 396.355, "duration": 6.99, "cleanText": [["what", "it", "require", "be", "proof", "of", "fraud", "and", "then", "it", "require", "proof", "that", "there", "be", "a", "connection", "between", "the", "fraud", "and", "the", "trading"]]}, {"text": "In this case, as I've said, there could be no closer connection.", "start": 396.355, "stop": 399.878, "duration": 3.52, "cleanText": [["in", "this", "case", "as", "I", "have", "say", "there", "could", "be", "no", "close", "connection"]]}, {"text": "It is only by the trading itself that the fraud is consummated, and that is exactly a connection that is picked up by the language of the statute.", "start": 399.878, "stop": 409.762, "duration": 9.88, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "only", "by", "the", "trading", "itself", "that", "the", "fraud", "be", "consummate", "and", "that", "be", "exactly", "a", "connection", "that", "be", "pick", "up", "by", "the", "language", "of", "the", "statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "What if Grand Met had its own strategy to purchase shares for some reason to make the price go up temporarily?", "start": 409.762, "stop": 418.227, "duration": 8.46, "cleanText": [["what", "if", "grand", "meet", "have", "its", "own", "strategy", "to", "purchase", "share", "for", "some", "reason", "to", "make", "the", "price", "go", "up", "temporarily"]]}, {"text": "I don't know quite how the hypothetical would play out, but suppose this was in Grand Met's interest, and yet all the facts were the same.", "start": 418.227, "stop": 425.654, "duration": 7.43, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "know", "quite", "how", "the", "hypothetical", "would", "play", "out", "but", "suppose", "this", "be", "in", "grand", "met", "s", "interest", "and", "yet", "all", "the", "fact", "we", "be", "the", "same"]]}, {"text": "The lawyer... it didn't know the lawyer was doing it.", "start": 425.654, "stop": 428.085, "duration": 2.43, "cleanText": [["the", "lawyer", "it", "do", "not", "know", "the", "lawyer", "be", "do", "it"]]}, {"text": "It was doing it on it's own, but what the lawyer did was also helping its grand scheme.", "start": 428.085, "stop": 431.628, "duration": 3.54, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "do", "it", "on", "it", "be", "own", "but", "what", "the", "lawyer", "do", "be", "also", "help", "its", "grand", "scheme"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "That--", "start": 431.628, "stop": 432.777, "duration": 1.15, "cleanText": [["that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would there be a misappropriation there?", "start": 432.777, "stop": 434.77, "duration": 1.99, "cleanText": [["would", "there", "be", "a", "misappropriation", "there"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes, there would.", "start": 434.77, "stop": 435.511, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["yes", "there", "would"]]}, {"text": "First of all that wouldn't have any effect on the violation that respondent committed on his law firm.", "start": 435.511, "stop": 441.833, "duration": 6.32, "cleanText": [["first", "of", "all", "that", "would", "not", "have", "any", "effect", "on", "the", "violation", "that", "respondent", "commit", "on", "his", "law", "firm"]]}, {"text": "He owed his law firm a duty of trust and confidence in addition to the duty he owed to the client, but more importantly than that, in this case there was no evidence that Grand Met knew about--", "start": 441.833, "stop": 454.141, "duration": 12.31, "cleanText": [["he", "owe", "his", "law", "firm", "a", "duty", "of", "trust", "and", "confidence", "in", "addition", "to", "the", "duty", "he", "owe", "to", "the", "client", "but", "more", "importantly", "than", "that", "in", "this", "case", "there", "be", "no", "evidence", "that", "grand", "meet", "knew", "about"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "But in the hypothetical you and I are discussing, if he came clean with the law firm and the whole law firm was doing it, then no violation?", "start": 454.141, "stop": 461.358, "duration": 7.22, "cleanText": [["but", "in", "the", "hypothetical", "you", "and", "i", "be", "discuss", "if", "he", "come", "clean", "with", "the", "law", "firm", "and", "the", "whole", "law", "firm", "be", "do", "it", "then", "no", "violation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--If he didn't deceive anyone by doing this, he would not--", "start": 461.358, "stop": 465.699, "duration": 4.34, "cleanText": [["if", "he", "do", "not", "deceive", "anyone", "by", "do", "this", "he", "would", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "What if he didn't tell the client.", "start": 465.699, "stop": 466.42, "duration": 0.72, "cleanText": [["what", "if", "he", "do", "not", "tell", "the", "client"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, then the client would be deceived.", "start": 466.42, "stop": 469.274, "duration": 2.85, "cleanText": [["well", "then", "the", "client", "would", "be", "deceive"]]}, {"text": "Whoever does not know about this and has not authorized it is a victim of the fraud, just as in the Carpenter case, if Weinans had gone to the Wall Street Journal and said, look, you know, you're not paying me very much.", "start": 469.274, "stop": 481.761, "duration": 12.49, "cleanText": [["whoever", "do", "not", "know", "about", "this", "and", "have", "not", "authorize", "it", "be", "a", "victim", "of", "the", "fraud", "just", "as", "in", "the", "carpenter", "case", "if", "weinans", "have", "go", "to", "the", "wall", "street", "journal", "and", "say", "look", "you", "know", "you", "be", "not", "pay", "me", "very", "much"]]}, {"text": "I'd like to make a little bit more money by buying stock, the stocks that are going to appear in my Heard on the Street column, and the Wall Street Journal said, that's fine, there would have been no deception of the Wall Street Journal.", "start": 481.761, "stop": 493.428, "duration": 11.67, "cleanText": [["I", "would", "like", "to", "make", "a", "little", "bit", "more", "money", "by", "buy", "stock", "the", "stock", "that", "be", "go", "to", "appear", "in", "my", "heard", "on", "the", "street", "column", "and", "the", "wall", "street", "journal", "say", "that", "be", "fine", "there", "would", "have", "be", "no", "deception", "of", "the", "wall", "street", "journal"]]}, {"text": "The statute does require deception, but there can be no doubt in a case like this that there is deception.", "start": 493.428, "stop": 500.252, "duration": 6.82, "cleanText": [["the", "statute", "do", "require", "deception", "but", "there", "can", "be", "no", "doubt", "in", "a", "case", "like", "this", "that", "there", "be", "deception"]]}, {"text": "This is the identical kind of fraudulent conduct that the Court had before it in the Carpenter case.", "start": 500.252, "stop": 505.726, "duration": 5.47, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "the", "identical", "kind", "of", "fraudulent", "conduct", "that", "the", "court", "have", "before", "it", "in", "the", "carpenter", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I'm not so sure I agree with you on that point, at least as to the... the Wall Street Journal in Carpenter was said to have a property interest in the confidentiality, or in the use of the notes for the column.", "start": 505.726, "stop": 521.618, "duration": 15.89, "cleanText": [["well", "I", "be", "not", "so", "sure", "i", "agree", "with", "you", "on", "that", "point", "at", "least", "as", "to", "the", "the", "wall", "street", "journal", "in", "carpenter", "be", "say", "to", "have", "a", "property", "interest", "in", "the", "confidentiality", "or", "in", "the", "use", "of", "the", "note", "for", "the", "column"]]}, {"text": "Here, there doesn't seem to be any property interest involved.", "start": 521.618, "stop": 524.88, "duration": 3.26, "cleanText": [["here", "there", "do", "not", "seem", "to", "be", "any", "property", "interest", "involve"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the property interest here is exactly the same as it was in Carpenter.", "start": 524.88, "stop": 529.412, "duration": 4.53, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "property", "interest", "here", "be", "exactly", "the", "same", "as", "it", "be", "in", "carpenter"]]}, {"text": "It's the information itself, which Grand Met has a right to determine how it would be used.", "start": 529.412, "stop": 536.296, "duration": 6.88, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "the", "information", "itself", "which", "grand", "met", "have", "a", "right", "to", "determine", "how", "it", "would", "be", "use"]]}, {"text": "It has a right to maintain its exclusive right to use the information and not to have the agents, upon whom it must rely if it's going to engage in any kind of business activity, misappropriate that information for personal gain, and I think it's a very well-settled concept of the common law and of the law of fraud that information is a species of property, so that--", "start": 536.296, "stop": 558.321, "duration": 22.02, "cleanText": [["it", "have", "a", "right", "to", "maintain", "its", "exclusive", "right", "to", "use", "the", "information", "and", "not", "to", "have", "the", "agent", "upon", "whom", "it", "must", "rely", "if", "it", "be", "go", "to", "engage", "in", "any", "kind", "of", "business", "activity", "misappropriate", "that", "information", "for", "personal", "gain", "and", "i", "think", "it", "be", "a", "very", "well", "settle", "concept", "of", "the", "common", "law", "and", "of", "the", "law", "of", "fraud", "that", "information", "be", "a", "specie", "of", "property", "so", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr.... I'm sorry.", "start": 558.321, "stop": 559.532, "duration": 1.21, "cleanText": [["mr"], ["I", "be", "sorry"]]}, {"text": "I didn't mean to interrupt.", "start": 559.532, "stop": 560.524, "duration": 0.99, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "mean", "to", "interrupt"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--So the deceptive conduct here is, in essence, indistinguishable from the deceptive conduct that the Court found in the Carpenter case.", "start": 560.524, "stop": 567.979, "duration": 7.46, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "deceptive", "conduct", "here", "be", "in", "essence", "indistinguishable", "from", "the", "deceptive", "conduct", "that", "the", "court", "find", "in", "the", "carpenter", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you take the position that every relationship of trust also implies the duty to disclose if the trust is to be breached?", "start": 567.979, "stop": 576.074, "duration": 8.09, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "take", "the", "position", "that", "every", "relationship", "of", "trust", "also", "imply", "the", "duty", "to", "disclose", "if", "the", "trust", "be", "to", "be", "breach"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't, Justice Souter.", "start": 576.074, "stop": 579.388, "duration": 3.31, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "justice", "souter"]]}, {"text": "I think that--", "start": 579.388, "stop": 580.199, "duration": 0.81, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "How do we know this is such a case and the others are not, then?", "start": 580.199, "stop": 583.587, "duration": 3.39, "cleanText": [["how", "do", "we", "know", "this", "be", "such", "a", "case", "and", "the", "others", "be", "not", "then"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, this is such a case because it involves a relationship right at the core of what has been defined as the principal agent-fiduciary trustee relationship.", "start": 583.587, "stop": 595.047, "duration": 11.46, "cleanText": [["well", "this", "be", "such", "a", "case", "because", "it", "involve", "a", "relationship", "right", "at", "the", "core", "of", "what", "have", "be", "define", "as", "the", "principal", "agent", "fiduciary", "trustee", "relationship"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, but so does a... I suppose a lawyer in a trust relationship with his client in the handling of funds, and yet if a lawyer... I presume that if a lawyer disclosed to his client that he was going to commingle, or he was going to borrow, as it were, the client's funds for personal reasons, that that would not be a defense either to a professional or a statutory charge against him.", "start": 595.047, "stop": 621.244, "duration": 26.2, "cleanText": [["well", "but", "so", "do", "a", "i", "suppose", "a", "lawyer", "in", "a", "trust", "relationship", "with", "his", "client", "in", "the", "handling", "of", "fund", "and", "yet", "if", "a", "lawyer", "i", "presume", "that", "if", "a", "lawyer", "disclose", "to", "his", "client", "that", "he", "be", "go", "to", "commingle", "or", "he", "be", "go", "to", "borrow", "as", "it", "we", "be", "the", "client", "s", "fund", "for", "personal", "reason", "that", "that", "would", "not", "be", "a", "defense", "either", "to", "a", "professional", "or", "a", "statutory", "charge", "against", "him"]]}, {"text": "Perhaps I'm wrong there, but I assumed it would not, so I'm not sure why, then, number 1 there is a disclosure obligation here, whereas a disclosure obligation there would be of no point--", "start": 621.244, "stop": 634.202, "duration": 12.96, "cleanText": [["perhaps", "I", "be", "wrong", "there", "but", "i", "assume", "it", "would", "not", "so", "I", "be", "not", "sure", "why", "then", "number", "there", "be", "a", "disclosure", "obligation", "here", "whereas", "a", "disclosure", "obligation", "there", "would", "be", "of", "no", "point"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "The--", "start": 634.202, "stop": 634.853, "duration": 0.65, "cleanText": [["the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "--and the one would be a defense and the other wouldn't.", "start": 634.853, "stop": 636.482, "duration": 1.63, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "one", "would", "be", "a", "defense", "and", "the", "other", "would", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Justice Souter, the reason why it makes a difference is that the disclosure obligation is a prerequisite to obtaining the consent of the principal or the owner of the trust.", "start": 636.482, "stop": 647.321, "duration": 10.84, "cleanText": [["justice", "souter", "the", "reason", "why", "it", "make", "a", "difference", "be", "that", "the", "disclosure", "obligation", "be", "a", "prerequisite", "to", "obtain", "the", "consent", "of", "the", "principal", "or", "the", "owner", "of", "the", "trust"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "But I thought... maybe I misunderstood your answer earlier.", "start": 647.321, "stop": 649.902, "duration": 2.58, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "think", "maybe", "i", "misunderstood", "your", "answer", "earlier"]]}, {"text": "I thought that if there were a disclosure but no consent that would in effect preclude liability.", "start": 649.902, "stop": 659.479, "duration": 9.58, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "if", "there", "we", "be", "a", "disclosure", "but", "no", "consent", "that", "would", "in", "effect", "preclude", "liability"]]}, {"text": "You're saying there must be a disclosure and consent.", "start": 659.479, "stop": 662.141, "duration": 2.66, "cleanText": [["you", "be", "say", "there", "must", "be", "a", "disclosure", "and", "consent"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "To satisfy the common law rule that a trustee may not use the property that's been entrusted with him, there would have to be consent.", "start": 662.141, "stop": 669.584, "duration": 7.44, "cleanText": [["to", "satisfy", "the", "common", "law", "rule", "that", "a", "trustee", "may", "not", "use", "the", "property", "that", "be", "be", "entrust", "with", "him", "there", "would", "have", "to", "be", "consent"]]}, {"text": "To satisfy the requirement of the Securities Act that there be no deception, there would only have to be disclosure.", "start": 669.584, "stop": 675.518, "duration": 5.93, "cleanText": [["to", "satisfy", "the", "requirement", "of", "the", "security", "act", "that", "there", "be", "no", "deception", "there", "would", "only", "have", "to", "be", "disclosure"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "I thought that was what you answered Justice Scalia when he asked the question.", "start": 675.518, "stop": 679.802, "duration": 4.28, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "be", "what", "you", "answer", "justice", "scalia", "when", "he", "ask", "the", "question"]]}, {"text": "Yes, that's what I thought, too.", "start": 679.802, "stop": 680.393, "duration": 0.59, "cleanText": [["yes", "that", "be", "what", "i", "think", "too"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 680.393, "stop": 680.712, "duration": 0.32, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "And... but there would be in that case other sanctions immediately.", "start": 680.712, "stop": 684.915, "duration": 4.2, "cleanText": [["and", "but", "there", "would", "be", "in", "that", "case", "other", "sanction", "immediately"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 684.915, "stop": 685.456, "duration": 0.54, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "If you told the law firm, look, I'm going to do this, the law firm isn't going to consent but it's not likely he'll retain his job, and there might be other sanctions.", "start": 685.456, "stop": 693.611, "duration": 8.15, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "tell", "the", "law", "firm", "look", "I", "be", "go", "to", "do", "this", "the", "law", "firm", "be", "not", "go", "to", "consent", "but", "it", "be", "not", "likely", "he", "will", "retain", "his", "job", "and", "there", "might", "be", "other", "sanction"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 693.611, "stop": 694.011, "duration": 0.4, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "It would still be--", "start": 694.011, "stop": 694.863, "duration": 0.85, "cleanText": [["it", "would", "still", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "In that case it's not 10(b)5.", "start": 694.863, "stop": 696.002, "duration": 1.14, "cleanText": [["in", "that", "case", "it", "be", "not", "b"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--It's not 10(b)5.", "start": 696.002, "stop": 696.833, "duration": 0.83, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "b"]]}, {"text": "It would still be a breach of fiduciary duty, but that makes the point that I'm trying to make here.", "start": 696.833, "stop": 701.267, "duration": 4.43, "cleanText": [["it", "would", "still", "be", "a", "breach", "of", "fiduciary", "duty", "but", "that", "make", "the", "point", "that", "I", "be", "try", "to", "make", "here"]]}, {"text": "Not every breach of fiduciary duty involves deception, but a breach of fiduciary duty when that breach involves the obligation to make disclosure does involve deception.", "start": 701.267, "stop": 712.333, "duration": 11.07, "cleanText": [["not", "every", "breach", "of", "fiduciary", "duty", "involve", "deception", "but", "a", "breach", "of", "fiduciary", "duty", "when", "that", "breach", "involve", "the", "obligation", "to", "make", "disclosure", "do", "involve", "deception"]]}, {"text": "That, in fact, is the foundation of this Court's rulings in Chiarella and Dirks that an insider in a corporation has a duty to his shareholders to make disclosure before trading with them.", "start": 712.333, "stop": 725.551, "duration": 13.22, "cleanText": [["that", "in", "fact", "be", "the", "foundation", "of", "this", "court", "s", "ruling", "in", "chiarella", "and", "dirks", "that", "an", "insider", "in", "a", "corporation", "have", "a", "duty", "to", "his", "shareholder", "to", "make", "disclosure", "before", "trading", "with", "them"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "There's one thing that I'm still not clear on, and that is, what is it that is peculiar about some breaches of trust, or some obligations of trust, that raise the disclosure obligation whereas others do not have a disclosure obligation that would at all be relevant?", "start": 725.551, "stop": 741.613, "duration": 16.06, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "one", "thing", "that", "I", "be", "still", "not", "clear", "on", "and", "that", "be", "what", "be", "it", "that", "be", "peculiar", "about", "some", "breach", "of", "trust", "or", "some", "obligation", "of", "trust", "that", "raise", "the", "disclosure", "obligation", "whereas", "others", "do", "not", "have", "a", "disclosure", "obligation", "that", "would", "at", "all", "be", "relevant"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "The answer, Justice Souter, is that there are some things that a trustee cannot do even if he does disclose them.", "start": 741.613, "stop": 750.078, "duration": 8.46, "cleanText": [["the", "answer", "justice", "souter", "be", "that", "there", "be", "some", "thing", "that", "a", "trustee", "can", "not", "do", "even", "if", "he", "do", "disclose", "them"]]}, {"text": "They will still be breaches of fiduciary duty, but there are some breaches of fiduciary duty that inherently require a breach of the duty to make disclosure.", "start": 750.078, "stop": 760.726, "duration": 10.65, "cleanText": [["they", "will", "still", "be", "breach", "of", "fiduciary", "duty", "but", "there", "be", "some", "breach", "of", "fiduciary", "duty", "that", "inherently", "require", "a", "breach", "of", "the", "duty", "to", "make", "disclosure"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "You rely on disclosure as just a reverse mechanism for defining deception.", "start": 760.726, "stop": 766.069, "duration": 5.34, "cleanText": [["you", "rely", "on", "disclosure", "as", "just", "a", "reverse", "mechanism", "for", "define", "deception"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Correct.", "start": 766.069, "stop": 767.379, "duration": 1.31, "cleanText": [["correct"]]}, {"text": "I think that it's clear under this Court's decisions in Chiarella and Dirks that generally silence is not fraudulent in conducting a transaction, but it becomes fraudulent if there is a duty to make disclosure, and the Court in the Chiarella and Dirks cases looked to well-settled understandings which it then believed were incorporated into 10(b) about when disclosure is required.", "start": 767.379, "stop": 793.117, "duration": 25.74, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "it", "be", "clear", "under", "this", "court", "s", "decision", "in", "chiarella", "and", "dirks", "that", "generally", "silence", "be", "not", "fraudulent", "in", "conduct", "a", "transaction", "but", "it", "become", "fraudulent", "if", "there", "be", "a", "duty", "to", "make", "disclosure", "and", "the", "court", "in", "the", "chiarella", "and", "dirks", "case", "look", "to", "well", "settle", "understanding", "which", "it", "then", "believe", "we", "be", "incorporate", "into", "b", "about", "when", "disclosure", "be", "require"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "If you read a horn-book on tort law does it say that the essence of deception is nondisclosure?", "start": 793.117, "stop": 799.161, "duration": 6.04, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "read", "a", "horn", "book", "on", "tort", "law", "do", "it", "say", "that", "the", "essence", "of", "deception", "be", "nondisclosure"]]}, {"text": "That's what you're asking us to write, I suppose.", "start": 799.161, "stop": 801.091, "duration": 1.93, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "what", "you", "be", "ask", "us", "to", "write", "i", "suppose"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm not asking the Court to do anything more than to reaffirm the basic principle that it adopted in Carpenter v. United States that an agent who misappropriates his principal's property by posing as a loyal employee when in fact he's reaping personal gain with that property has committed a form of deception, indeed, a form of fraud, and that fraud satisfies both the mail fraud statute and it satisfies section 10(b).", "start": 801.091, "stop": 828.009, "duration": 26.92, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "not", "ask", "the", "court", "to", "do", "anything", "more", "than", "to", "reaffirm", "the", "basic", "principle", "that", "it", "adopt", "in", "carpenter", "v", "united", "state", "that", "an", "agent", "who", "misappropriate", "his", "principal", "s", "property", "by", "pose", "as", "a", "loyal", "employee", "when", "in", "fact", "he", "be", "reap", "personal", "gain", "with", "that", "property", "have", "commit", "a", "form", "of", "deception", "indeed", "a", "form", "of", "fraud", "and", "that", "fraud", "satisfies", "both", "the", "mail", "fraud", "statute", "and", "it", "satisfy", "section", "b"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "May I ask you one question, Mr. Dreeben?", "start": 828.009, "stop": 830.373, "duration": 2.36, "cleanText": [["may", "i", "ask", "you", "one", "question", "mr", "dreeben"]]}, {"text": "I'm a little puzzled by your statement that... if I understood you correctly, that if the defendant here had disclosed to his partners, that would have avoided liability, and you're suggesting there was therefore no duty to disclose to the client.", "start": 830.373, "stop": 844.341, "duration": 13.97, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "a", "little", "puzzle", "by", "your", "statement", "that", "if", "i", "understand", "you", "correctly", "that", "if", "the", "defendant", "here", "have", "disclose", "to", "his", "partner", "that", "would", "have", "avoid", "liability", "and", "you", "be", "suggest", "there", "be", "therefore", "no", "duty", "to", "disclose", "to", "the", "client"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, I think there is a duty to disclose to the client as well.", "start": 844.341, "stop": 848.815, "duration": 4.47, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "think", "there", "be", "a", "duty", "to", "disclose", "to", "the", "client", "as", "well"]]}, {"text": "I think that there are two victims, direct victims of the deception.", "start": 848.815, "stop": 852.886, "duration": 4.07, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "there", "be", "two", "victim", "direct", "victim", "of", "the", "deception"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "But supposing in this case he had disclosed to his partner, and his partner had just kept the information to himself, and then he had gone... the defendant had gone ahead with his trading.", "start": 852.886, "stop": 861.061, "duration": 8.18, "cleanText": [["but", "suppose", "in", "this", "case", "he", "have", "disclose", "to", "his", "partner", "and", "his", "partner", "have", "just", "keep", "the", "information", "to", "himself", "and", "then", "he", "have", "go", "the", "defendant", "have", "go", "ahead", "with", "his", "trading"]]}, {"text": "Would there be a violation?", "start": 861.061, "stop": 862.603, "duration": 1.54, "cleanText": [["would", "there", "be", "a", "violation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, there would, but we would not have been able to charge it the same way as we charged this case.", "start": 862.603, "stop": 867.265, "duration": 4.66, "cleanText": [["yes", "there", "would", "but", "we", "would", "not", "have", "be", "able", "to", "charge", "it", "the", "same", "way", "as", "we", "charge", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "I see.", "start": 867.265, "stop": 867.575, "duration": 0.31, "cleanText": [["i", "see"]]}, {"text": "You then would have said there was a breach of the firm's duty to the client.", "start": 867.575, "stop": 869.697, "duration": 2.12, "cleanText": [["you", "then", "would", "have", "say", "there", "be", "a", "breach", "of", "the", "firm", "s", "duty", "to", "the", "client"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 869.697, "stop": 870.508, "duration": 0.81, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "In this case, the jury was instructed that it could rely on a finding of a breach of duty either to the law firm or to the client or to both, and it had to be unanimous about which one it found, but it had to find one or the other, or it could find both, and if there was disclosure, the party that received the disclosure would not be a victim of the fraud on our theory.", "start": 870.508, "stop": 890.31, "duration": 19.8, "cleanText": [["in", "this", "case", "the", "jury", "be", "instruct", "that", "it", "could", "rely", "on", "a", "finding", "of", "a", "breach", "of", "duty", "either", "to", "the", "law", "firm", "or", "to", "the", "client", "or", "to", "both", "and", "it", "have", "to", "be", "unanimous", "about", "which", "one", "it", "find", "but", "it", "have", "to", "find", "one", "or", "the", "other", "or", "it", "could", "find", "both", "and", "if", "there", "be", "disclosure", "the", "party", "that", "receive", "the", "disclosure", "would", "not", "be", "a", "victim", "of", "the", "fraud", "on", "our", "theory"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Dreeben--", "start": 890.31, "stop": 891.301, "duration": 0.99, "cleanText": [["mr", "dreeben"]]}, {"text": "--Now, Mr. Dreeben, we... this Court has always required either a misrepresentation or an omission to find 10(b) liability, I think, and you say there was an omission here by the failure to disclose.", "start": 891.301, "stop": 907.831, "duration": 16.53, "cleanText": [["now", "mr", "dreeben", "we", "this", "court", "have", "always", "require", "either", "a", "misrepresentation", "or", "an", "omission", "to", "find", "b", "liability", "i", "think", "and", "you", "say", "there", "be", "an", "omission", "here", "by", "the", "failure", "to", "disclose"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, and I say that there is an omission by the failure to disclose in exactly the same way as there was in Carpenter.", "start": 907.831, "stop": 914.937, "duration": 7.11, "cleanText": [["yes", "and", "i", "say", "that", "there", "be", "an", "omission", "by", "the", "failure", "to", "disclose", "in", "exactly", "the", "same", "way", "as", "there", "be", "in", "carpenter"]]}, {"text": "I also believe that the Court has never ruled out what seems commonsensical under 10(b), the idea that the conduct itself, even without a statement or an omission, can be deceptive.", "start": 914.937, "stop": 928.435, "duration": 13.5, "cleanText": [["i", "also", "believe", "that", "the", "court", "have", "never", "rule", "out", "what", "seem", "commonsensical", "under", "b", "the", "idea", "that", "the", "conduct", "itself", "even", "without", "a", "statement", "or", "an", "omission", "can", "be", "deceptive"]]}, {"text": "I mean, here you have a lawyer who worked in his firm, came to work every day posing as a loyal partner, engaging his partners in discussions about firm business, under the understanding that he was doing this in the interests of the firm, when in fact, as the jury concluded, he used the information that he acquired to finance... to enable his own securities purchases and to profit--", "start": 928.435, "stop": 953.031, "duration": 24.6, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "here", "you", "have", "a", "lawyer", "who", "work", "in", "his", "firm", "come", "to", "work", "every", "day", "pose", "as", "a", "loyal", "partner", "engage", "his", "partner", "in", "discussion", "about", "firm", "business", "under", "the", "understanding", "that", "he", "be", "do", "this", "in", "the", "interest", "of", "the", "firm", "when", "in", "fact", "as", "the", "jury", "conclude", "he", "use", "the", "information", "that", "he", "acquire", "to", "finance", "to", "enable", "his", "own", "security", "purchase", "and", "to", "profit"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, any, any fraud is deception, then.", "start": 953.031, "stop": 955.034, "duration": 2, "cleanText": [["well", "any", "any", "fraud", "be", "deception", "then"]]}, {"text": "I assume that, you know, if a lawyer takes the client's money that's supposed to be in a trust account and just removes it posing as an honest lawyer, I mean, you know, everybody who commits any fraud is guilty of deception.", "start": 955.034, "stop": 970.272, "duration": 15.24, "cleanText": [["i", "assume", "that", "you", "know", "if", "a", "lawyer", "take", "the", "client", "s", "money", "that", "be", "suppose", "to", "be", "in", "a", "trust", "account", "and", "just", "remove", "it", "pose", "as", "an", "honest", "lawyer", "i", "mean", "you", "know", "everybody", "who", "commit", "any", "fraud", "be", "guilty", "of", "deception"]]}, {"text": "Isn't that right?", "start": 970.272, "stop": 970.843, "duration": 0.57, "cleanText": [["be", "not", "that", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--And the Court... yes, Justice Scalia, and the Court said--", "start": 970.843, "stop": 973.494, "duration": 2.65, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "court", "yes", "justice", "scalia", "and", "the", "court", "say"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "What if I appropriate some of my client's money in order to buy stock?", "start": 973.494, "stop": 978.078, "duration": 4.58, "cleanText": [["what", "if", "i", "appropriate", "some", "of", "my", "client", "s", "money", "in", "order", "to", "buy", "stock"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The fact--", "start": 978.078, "stop": 981.77, "duration": 3.69, "cleanText": [["the", "fact"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Have I violated the securities laws?", "start": 981.77, "stop": 983.222, "duration": 1.45, "cleanText": [["have", "i", "violate", "the", "security", "law"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I do not think that you have.", "start": 983.222, "stop": 985.693, "duration": 2.47, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "that", "you", "have"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why not?", "start": 985.693, "stop": 986.354, "duration": 0.66, "cleanText": [["why", "not"]]}, {"text": "Isn't that in connection with the purchase of security just as much as this one is?", "start": 986.354, "stop": 991.897, "duration": 5.54, "cleanText": [["be", "not", "that", "in", "connection", "with", "the", "purchase", "of", "security", "just", "as", "much", "as", "this", "one", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "It's not just as much as this one is, because in this case it is the use of the information that enables the profits, pure and simple.", "start": 991.897, "stop": 999.422, "duration": 7.52, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "just", "as", "much", "as", "this", "one", "be", "because", "in", "this", "case", "it", "be", "the", "use", "of", "the", "information", "that", "enable", "the", "profit", "pure", "and", "simple"]]}, {"text": "There would be no opportunity to engage in profit--", "start": 999.422, "stop": 1002.313, "duration": 2.89, "cleanText": [["there", "would", "be", "no", "opportunity", "to", "engage", "in", "profit"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Same here.", "start": 1002.313, "stop": 1003.054, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["same", "here"]]}, {"text": "I didn't have the money.", "start": 1003.054, "stop": 1003.906, "duration": 0.85, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "have", "the", "money"]]}, {"text": "The only way I could buy this stock was to get the money.", "start": 1003.906, "stop": 1007.148, "duration": 3.24, "cleanText": [["the", "only", "way", "i", "could", "buy", "this", "stock", "be", "to", "get", "the", "money"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The difference--", "start": 1007.148, "stop": 1007.749, "duration": 0.6, "cleanText": [["the", "difference"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "And I got the money posing as an honest lawyer.", "start": 1007.749, "stop": 1011.439, "duration": 3.69, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "get", "the", "money", "posing", "as", "an", "honest", "lawyer"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The difference, Justice Scalia, is that once you have the money you can do anything you want with it.", "start": 1011.439, "stop": 1014.961, "duration": 3.52, "cleanText": [["the", "difference", "justice", "scalia", "be", "that", "once", "you", "have", "the", "money", "you", "can", "do", "anything", "you", "want", "with", "it"]]}, {"text": "In a sense, the fraud is complete at that point, and then you go on and you can use the money to finance any number of other activities, but the connection is far less close than in this case, where the only value of this information for persona profit for respondent was to take it and profit in the securities markets by trading on it.", "start": 1014.961, "stop": 1034.336, "duration": 19.38, "cleanText": [["in", "a", "sense", "the", "fraud", "be", "complete", "at", "that", "point", "and", "then", "you", "go", "on", "and", "you", "can", "use", "the", "money", "to", "finance", "any", "number", "of", "other", "activity", "but", "the", "connection", "be", "far", "less", "close", "than", "in", "this", "case", "where", "the", "only", "value", "of", "this", "information", "for", "persona", "profit", "for", "respondent", "be", "to", "take", "it", "and", "profit", "in", "the", "security", "market", "by", "trade", "on", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why isn't the client entrusted just as totally when he entrusts money as when he entrusts information?", "start": 1034.336, "stop": 1042.8, "duration": 8.46, "cleanText": [["why", "be", "not", "the", "client", "entrust", "just", "as", "totally", "when", "he", "entrust", "money", "as", "when", "he", "entrust", "information"]]}, {"text": "I don't under... I guess my problem is--", "start": 1042.8, "stop": 1044.751, "duration": 1.95, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "under", "i", "guess", "my", "problem", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "He does, Justice Souter.", "start": 1044.751, "stop": 1045.472, "duration": 0.72, "cleanText": [["he", "do", "justice", "souter"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "--the same as Justice Scalia's.", "start": 1045.472, "stop": 1046.002, "duration": 0.53, "cleanText": [["the", "same", "as", "justice", "scalia", "s"]]}, {"text": "I don't... if we're starting with a breach of trust, I don't see why a breach of trust with respect to a fact which is communicated gives rise to a disclosure obligation when a breach of trust with respect to some other thing of value, e.g., the contents of the trust account, does not.", "start": 1046.002, "stop": 1066.326, "duration": 20.32, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "if", "we", "be", "start", "with", "a", "breach", "of", "trust", "i", "do", "not", "see", "why", "a", "breach", "of", "trust", "with", "respect", "to", "a", "fact", "which", "be", "communicate", "give", "rise", "to", "a", "disclosure", "obligation", "when", "a", "breach", "of", "trust", "with", "respect", "to", "some", "other", "thing", "of", "value", "eg", "the", "content", "of", "the", "trust", "account", "do", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "I perhaps was not clear in answering Justice Scalia, Justice Souter.", "start": 1066.326, "stop": 1070.23, "duration": 3.9, "cleanText": [["i", "perhaps", "be", "not", "clear", "in", "answer", "justice", "scalia", "justice", "souter"]]}, {"text": "It is just as much of a breach, and it is just as much fraudulent and deceptive, and that, in fact, is what the Court said in Carpenter.", "start": 1070.23, "stop": 1078.335, "duration": 8.11, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "just", "as", "much", "of", "a", "breach", "and", "it", "be", "just", "as", "much", "fraudulent", "and", "deceptive", "and", "that", "in", "fact", "be", "what", "the", "court", "say", "in", "carpenter"]]}, {"text": "Embezzlement is a form of fraud.", "start": 1078.335, "stop": 1081.807, "duration": 3.47, "cleanText": [["embezzlement", "be", "a", "form", "of", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "The question is whether that fraud is in connection with the purchase or sale of the security, and the question is whether that form of fraud which I submit is complete at the time the money is obtained is in connection with the purchase or sale versus this one.", "start": 1081.807, "stop": 1097.055, "duration": 15.25, "cleanText": [["the", "question", "be", "whether", "that", "fraud", "be", "in", "connection", "with", "the", "purchase", "or", "sale", "of", "the", "security", "and", "the", "question", "be", "whether", "that", "form", "of", "fraud", "which", "i", "submit", "be", "complete", "at", "the", "time", "the", "money", "be", "obtain", "be", "in", "connection", "with", "the", "purchase", "or", "sale", "versus", "this", "one"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "So that every breach does give rise to a duty to disclose.", "start": 1097.055, "stop": 1100.477, "duration": 3.42, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "every", "breach", "do", "give", "rise", "to", "a", "duty", "to", "disclose"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Every breach that involves the misuse of information entrusted to a person or the misuse of property entrusted to a person--", "start": 1100.477, "stop": 1108.852, "duration": 8.38, "cleanText": [["every", "breach", "that", "involve", "the", "misuse", "of", "information", "entrust", "to", "a", "person", "or", "the", "misuse", "of", "property", "entrust", "to", "a", "person"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1108.852, "stop": 1109.223, "duration": 0.37, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--for personal gain, yes.", "start": 1109.223, "stop": 1110.274, "duration": 1.05, "cleanText": [["for", "personal", "gain", "yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Okay.", "start": 1110.274, "stop": 1110.665, "duration": 0.39, "cleanText": [["okay"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's hornbook law, and I don't think that there's any dispute about that at all.", "start": 1110.665, "stop": 1114.498, "duration": 3.83, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "hornbook", "law", "and", "i", "do", "not", "think", "that", "there", "be", "any", "dispute", "about", "that", "at", "all"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "So what you're saying is, is in this case the misappropriation can only be of relevance, or is of substantial relevance, is with reference to the purchase of securities.", "start": 1114.498, "stop": 1124.184, "duration": 9.69, "cleanText": [["so", "what", "you", "be", "say", "be", "be", "in", "this", "case", "the", "misappropriation", "can", "only", "be", "of", "relevance", "or", "be", "of", "substantial", "relevance", "be", "with", "reference", "to", "the", "purchase", "of", "security"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Exactly.", "start": 1124.184, "stop": 1124.885, "duration": 0.7, "cleanText": [["exactly"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "When you take the money out of the accounts you can go to the racetrack, or whatever--", "start": 1124.885, "stop": 1128.568, "duration": 3.68, "cleanText": [["when", "you", "take", "the", "money", "out", "of", "the", "account", "you", "can", "go", "to", "the", "racetrack", "or", "whatever"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's exactly right, and because of that difference, three can be no doubt that this kind of misappropriation of property is in connection with the purchase or sale of securities.", "start": 1128.568, "stop": 1141.015, "duration": 12.45, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "exactly", "right", "and", "because", "of", "that", "difference", "three", "can", "be", "no", "doubt", "that", "this", "kind", "of", "misappropriation", "of", "property", "be", "in", "connection", "with", "the", "purchase", "or", "sale", "of", "security"]]}, {"text": "Other kinds of misappropriation of property may or may not, but this is a unique form of fraud, unique to the securities markets, in fact, because the only way in which respondent could have profited through this information is by either trading on it or by tipping somebody else to enable their trades.", "start": 1141.015, "stop": 1159.175, "duration": 18.16, "cleanText": [["other", "kind", "of", "misappropriation", "of", "property", "may", "or", "may", "not", "but", "this", "be", "a", "unique", "form", "of", "fraud", "unique", "to", "the", "security", "market", "in", "fact", "because", "the", "only", "way", "in", "which", "respondent", "could", "have", "profit", "through", "this", "information", "be", "by", "either", "trading", "on", "it", "or", "by", "tip", "somebody", "else", "to", "enable", "their", "trade"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "--With respect to the tip, I wasn't quite sure of your answer to Justice O'Connor when she brought up the child.", "start": 1159.175, "stop": 1166.722, "duration": 7.55, "cleanText": [["with", "respect", "to", "the", "tip", "i", "be", "not", "quite", "sure", "of", "your", "answer", "to", "justice", "oconnor", "when", "she", "bring", "up", "the", "child"]]}, {"text": "Were you responding to her word inadvertent, because if this parent tipped off the child and told the child to purchase the security, surely there would be--", "start": 1166.722, "stop": 1178.199, "duration": 11.48, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "you", "respond", "to", "her", "word", "inadvertent", "because", "if", "this", "parent", "tip", "off", "the", "child", "and", "tell", "the", "child", "to", "purchase", "the", "security", "surely", "there", "would", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1178.199, "stop": 1179.879, "duration": 1.68, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "--responsibility.", "start": 1179.879, "stop": 1180.63, "duration": 0.75, "cleanText": [["responsibility"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, there would.", "start": 1180.63, "stop": 1181.271, "duration": 0.64, "cleanText": [["yes", "there", "would"]]}, {"text": "In a case like that, Justice Ginsburg, a fiduciary cannot do indirectly what he's prohibited from doing directly, and so using the child as the medium for conducting the transaction would be equally forbidden.", "start": 1181.271, "stop": 1196.131, "duration": 14.86, "cleanText": [["in", "a", "case", "like", "that", "justice", "ginsburg", "a", "fiduciary", "can", "not", "do", "indirectly", "what", "he", "be", "prohibit", "from", "do", "directly", "and", "so", "use", "the", "child", "as", "the", "medium", "for", "conduct", "the", "transaction", "would", "be", "equally", "forbidden"]]}, {"text": "I think Justice O'Connor's question was getting at the point about whether the child would be committing fraud on the parent if the child engaged in this trading after having learned inadvertently--", "start": 1196.131, "stop": 1208.66, "duration": 12.53, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "justice", "oconnor", "s", "question", "be", "get", "at", "the", "point", "about", "whether", "the", "child", "would", "be", "commit", "fraud", "on", "the", "parent", "if", "the", "child", "engage", "in", "this", "trading", "after", "have", "learn", "inadvertently"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 1208.66, "stop": 1209.068, "duration": 0.41, "cleanText": [["right"]]}, {"text": "Now--", "start": 1209.068, "stop": 1209.649, "duration": 0.58, "cleanText": [["now"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--of the information, and I--", "start": 1209.649, "stop": 1210.5, "duration": 0.85, "cleanText": [["of", "the", "information", "and", "i"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Let me ask you whether you think section 14(e) provides you with an easier argument for liability than 10(b).", "start": 1210.5, "stop": 1221.686, "duration": 11.19, "cleanText": [["let", "me", "ask", "you", "whether", "you", "think", "section", "e", "provide", "you", "with", "an", "easy", "argument", "for", "liability", "than", "b"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, I certainly think that 14(e) provides us with a perfectly valid argument for liability.", "start": 1221.686, "stop": 1228.272, "duration": 6.59, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "certainly", "think", "that", "e", "provide", "us", "with", "a", "perfectly", "valid", "argument", "for", "liability"]]}, {"text": "The theory under section 14 is that Congress specifically gave the Commission regulatory authority in the area of tender offers because it recognized that tender offers pose a very significant threat to investors in the target company having the ability to make decisions about whether to buy, sell, or hold when a tender offer is on the horizon.", "start": 1228.272, "stop": 1254.64, "duration": 26.37, "cleanText": [["the", "theory", "under", "section", "be", "that", "congress", "specifically", "give", "the", "commission", "regulatory", "authority", "in", "the", "area", "of", "tender", "offer", "because", "it", "recognize", "that", "tender", "offer", "pose", "a", "very", "significant", "threat", "to", "investor", "in", "the", "target", "company", "have", "the", "ability", "to", "make", "decision", "about", "whether", "to", "buy", "sell", "or", "hold", "when", "a", "tender", "offer", "be", "on", "the", "horizon"]]}, {"text": "Congress also knew that there is a great opportunity for insider profiting because the information about a tender offer is necessarily circulated to many professionals in advance of the tender offer who then have the opportunity to go out and trade on it, and as a result of its recognition about the dangers of fraudulent and deceptive practices and tender offers, Congress was not content to rely simply on section 10(b) but drafted a new and different antifraud provision which is backed up by regulatory authority that gives the SEC the power to define and prescribe means reasonably designed to prevent fraudulent, deceptive, manipulative conduct.", "start": 1254.64, "stop": 1298.136, "duration": 43.5, "cleanText": [["congress", "also", "know", "that", "there", "be", "a", "great", "opportunity", "for", "insider", "profiting", "because", "the", "information", "about", "a", "tender", "offer", "be", "necessarily", "circulate", "to", "many", "professional", "in", "advance", "of", "the", "tender", "offer", "who", "then", "have", "the", "opportunity", "to", "go", "out", "and", "trade", "on", "it", "and", "as", "a", "result", "of", "its", "recognition", "about", "the", "danger", "of", "fraudulent", "and", "deceptive", "practice", "and", "tender", "offer", "congress", "be", "not", "content", "to", "rely", "simply", "on", "section", "b", "but", "draft", "a", "new", "and", "different", "antifraud", "provision", "which", "be", "back", "up", "by", "regulatory", "authority", "that", "give", "the", "sec", "the", "power", "to", "define", "and", "prescribe", "mean", "reasonably", "design", "to", "prevent", "fraudulent", "deceptive", "manipulative", "conduct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "You omitted one little part there from that sentence, Mr. Dreeben... designed to prevent such acts and practices as are fraudulent, deceptive, or manipulative.", "start": 1298.136, "stop": 1307.533, "duration": 9.4, "cleanText": [["you", "omit", "one", "little", "part", "there", "from", "that", "sentence", "mr", "dreeben", "design", "to", "prevent", "such", "act", "and", "practice", "as", "be", "fraudulent", "deceptive", "or", "manipulative"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct, Justice--", "start": 1307.533, "stop": 1308.494, "duration": 0.96, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "justice"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "And it seems to me one could read that as saying that that does not give the SEC authority to define what is fraudulent, what is deceptive or manipulative, but simply to define practices which are in fact fraudulent, and you can't expand on the definition of fraudulent or deceptive.", "start": 1308.494, "stop": 1326.757, "duration": 18.26, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "one", "could", "read", "that", "as", "say", "that", "that", "do", "not", "give", "the", "sec", "authority", "to", "define", "what", "be", "fraudulent", "what", "be", "deceptive", "or", "manipulative", "but", "simply", "to", "define", "practice", "which", "be", "in", "fact", "fraudulent", "and", "you", "can", "not", "expand", "on", "the", "definition", "of", "fraudulent", "or", "deceptive"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--There are several reasons, Chief Justice Rehnquist, why I think that you're correct that I omitted the words, acts or practices as are fraudulent, but I think that the statute is accurately paraphrased the way that I read it.", "start": 1326.757, "stop": 1340.585, "duration": 13.83, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "several", "reason", "chief", "justice", "rehnquist", "why", "i", "think", "that", "you", "be", "correct", "that", "i", "omit", "the", "word", "act", "or", "practice", "as", "be", "fraudulent", "but", "i", "think", "that", "the", "statute", "be", "accurately", "paraphrase", "the", "way", "that", "i", "read", "it"]]}, {"text": "First, the regulatory authority that is found in section 14(e) was modeled on a different section of the securities laws, not section 10(b), but section 15(c), which dealt with regulating broker-dealers, and in that context Congress had specifically given the SEC the authority to define fraudulent practices because it wanted to establish a higher standard of obligations and duties than would otherwise be imposed by the common law.", "start": 1340.585, "stop": 1369.634, "duration": 29.05, "cleanText": [["first", "the", "regulatory", "authority", "that", "be", "find", "in", "section", "e", "be", "model", "on", "a", "different", "section", "of", "the", "security", "law", "not", "section", "b", "but", "section", "c", "which", "deal", "with", "regulate", "broker", "dealer", "and", "in", "that", "context", "congress", "have", "specifically", "give", "the", "sec", "the", "authority", "to", "define", "fraudulent", "practice", "because", "it", "want", "to", "establish", "a", "high", "standard", "of", "obligation", "and", "duty", "than", "would", "otherwise", "be", "impose", "by", "the", "common", "law"]]}, {"text": "It adopted that language in section 14(e) after the SEC had previously exercised its power to create new obligations that weren't found in the common law, unless it's reasonable to infer that Congress expected that authority to be exercised in that fashion.", "start": 1369.634, "stop": 1386.344, "duration": 16.71, "cleanText": [["it", "adopt", "that", "language", "in", "section", "e", "after", "the", "sec", "have", "previously", "exercise", "its", "power", "to", "create", "new", "obligation", "that", "be", "not", "find", "in", "the", "common", "law", "unless", "it", "be", "reasonable", "to", "infer", "that", "congress", "expect", "that", "authority", "to", "be", "exercise", "in", "that", "fashion"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, except, now, the Schreiber case indicated that the SEC can't define offensive conduct more broadly than the statute provides.", "start": 1386.344, "stop": 1399.534, "duration": 13.19, "cleanText": [["well", "except", "now", "the", "schreiber", "case", "indicate", "that", "the", "sec", "can", "not", "define", "offensive", "conduct", "more", "broadly", "than", "the", "statute", "provide"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Actually the Schreiber case, Justice O'Connor, didn't involve any SEC regulation at all.", "start": 1399.534, "stop": 1404.386, "duration": 4.85, "cleanText": [["actually", "the", "schreiber", "case", "justice", "oconnor", "do", "not", "involve", "any", "sec", "regulation", "at", "all"]]}, {"text": "It involved simply the question about whether a fully disclosed act would be deemed manipulative under the first sentence of section 14(e).", "start": 1404.386, "stop": 1414.604, "duration": 10.22, "cleanText": [["it", "involve", "simply", "the", "question", "about", "whether", "a", "fully", "disclose", "act", "would", "be", "deem", "manipulative", "under", "the", "first", "sentence", "of", "section", "e"]]}, {"text": "There were no regulations at issue in the case whatsoever.", "start": 1414.604, "stop": 1417.897, "duration": 3.29, "cleanText": [["there", "we", "be", "no", "regulation", "at", "issue", "in", "the", "case", "whatsoever"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "But there certainly is language in that opinion.", "start": 1417.897, "stop": 1420.917, "duration": 3.02, "cleanText": [["but", "there", "certainly", "be", "language", "in", "that", "opinion"]]}, {"text": "I think footnote 11 indicates that SEC can't go more broadly than the terms of the statute.", "start": 1420.917, "stop": 1429.744, "duration": 8.83, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "footnote", "indicates", "that", "sec", "can", "not", "go", "more", "broadly", "than", "the", "term", "of", "the", "statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think the footnote, read in context, says that the mere promulgation of the regulatory authority for the SEC, the addition of the sentence that gave the SEC regulatory authority, didn't change the meanings of the words in the first sentence, but the Court expressly recognized that Congress had authority... that Congress had given authority to the SEC not only to define acts or practices as are fraudulent but to prescribe means reasonably designed to prevent them, and the Court explicitly said there that the SEC could prohibit nondeceptive conduct as a means reasonably designed to prevent fraud.", "start": 1429.744, "stop": 1470.25, "duration": 40.51, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "the", "footnote", "read", "in", "context", "say", "that", "the", "mere", "promulgation", "of", "the", "regulatory", "authority", "for", "the", "sec", "the", "addition", "of", "the", "sentence", "that", "give", "the", "sec", "regulatory", "authority", "do", "not", "change", "the", "meaning", "of", "the", "word", "in", "the", "first", "sentence", "but", "the", "court", "expressly", "recognize", "that", "congress", "have", "authority", "that", "congress", "have", "give", "authority", "to", "the", "sec", "not", "only", "to", "define", "act", "or", "practice", "as", "be", "fraudulent", "but", "to", "prescribe", "mean", "reasonably", "design", "to", "prevent", "them", "and", "the", "court", "explicitly", "say", "there", "that", "the", "sec", "could", "prohibit", "nondeceptive", "conduct", "as", "a", "mean", "reasonably", "design", "to", "prevent", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "So the Court in Schreiber I think did acknowledge that the SEC has very vast regulatory power in order to protect against the abuses that Congress had identified in the tender offer context.", "start": 1470.25, "stop": 1483.347, "duration": 13.1, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "court", "in", "schreiber", "i", "think", "do", "acknowledge", "that", "the", "sec", "have", "very", "vast", "regulatory", "power", "in", "order", "to", "protect", "against", "the", "abuse", "that", "congress", "have", "identify", "in", "the", "tender", "offer", "context"]]}, {"text": "Rule 14(e) 3 does that by establishing a flat ban on trading by persons who come into possession of information about an upcoming tender offer when they know that it was received from the bidder or somebody acting on its behalf, and that flat ban serves two valuable purposes.", "start": 1483.347, "stop": 1504.961, "duration": 21.61, "cleanText": [["rule", "e", "do", "that", "by", "establish", "a", "flat", "ban", "on", "trading", "by", "person", "who", "come", "into", "possession", "of", "information", "about", "an", "upcoming", "tender", "offer", "when", "they", "know", "that", "it", "be", "receive", "from", "the", "bidder", "or", "somebody", "act", "on", "its", "behalf", "and", "that", "flat", "ban", "serf", "two", "valuable", "purpose"]]}, {"text": "The first is that it protects shareholders who are going to be facing a tender offer, or who actually are facing a tender offer, from not having adequate time and adequate information to make a decision whether to buy, sell, or hold.", "start": 1504.961, "stop": 1521.554, "duration": 16.59, "cleanText": [["the", "first", "be", "that", "it", "protect", "shareholder", "who", "be", "go", "to", "be", "face", "a", "tender", "offer", "or", "who", "actually", "be", "face", "a", "tender", "offer", "from", "not", "have", "adequate", "time", "and", "adequate", "information", "to", "make", "a", "decision", "whether", "to", "buy", "sell", "or", "hold"]]}, {"text": "It also prevents collusion between the bidder and other parties operating in the marketplace that has not disclosed to the marketplace, as the Williams Act requires, from buying up stock from unsuspecting shareholders in the target company.", "start": 1521.554, "stop": 1535.883, "duration": 14.33, "cleanText": [["it", "also", "prevent", "collusion", "between", "the", "bidder", "and", "other", "party", "operate", "in", "the", "marketplace", "that", "have", "not", "disclose", "to", "the", "marketplace", "as", "the", "williams", "act", "require", "from", "buy", "up", "stock", "from", "unsuspecting", "shareholder", "in", "the", "target", "company"]]}, {"text": "A second purpose that is served by 14(e)3 is the prevention of fraudulent activity that involves, as this case did, the deceptive acquisition of information from the bidder or law firm's accountants, investment bankers that represent it, and it thereby serves to prevent that kind of fraud from occurring, which is a very great danger, and which involves a very great danger of not being detected, because this is in essence a crime that involves surreptitious activity that is not often easy to bring to light.", "start": 1535.883, "stop": 1573.397, "duration": 37.51, "cleanText": [["a", "second", "purpose", "that", "be", "serve", "by", "e", "be", "the", "prevention", "of", "fraudulent", "activity", "that", "involve", "as", "this", "case", "do", "the", "deceptive", "acquisition", "of", "information", "from", "the", "bidder", "or", "law", "firm", "s", "accountant", "investment", "banker", "that", "represent", "it", "and", "it", "thereby", "serve", "to", "prevent", "that", "kind", "of", "fraud", "from", "occur", "which", "be", "a", "very", "great", "danger", "and", "which", "involve", "a", "very", "great", "danger", "of", "not", "be", "detect", "because", "this", "be", "in", "essence", "a", "crime", "that", "involve", "surreptitious", "activity", "that", "be", "not", "often", "easy", "to", "bring", "to", "light"]]}, {"text": "So 14(e)3 carves out in the tender offer context very special heightened rules.", "start": 1573.397, "stop": 1580.192, "duration": 6.8, "cleanText": [["so", "e", "carves", "out", "in", "the", "tender", "offer", "context", "very", "special", "heighten", "rule"]]}, {"text": "It carves out and creates in the tender offer context a disclose or abstain from trading obligation, but it does not apply, as section 10(b) does, to the rest of the universe of securities transactions in which the misuse of information can pose very serious threats.", "start": 1580.192, "stop": 1598.024, "duration": 17.83, "cleanText": [["it", "carve", "out", "and", "creates", "in", "the", "tender", "offer", "context", "a", "disclose", "or", "abstain", "from", "trade", "obligation", "but", "it", "do", "not", "apply", "as", "section", "b", "do", "to", "the", "rest", "of", "the", "universe", "of", "security", "transaction", "in", "which", "the", "misuse", "of", "information", "can", "pose", "very", "serious", "threat"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, 10(e) perhaps does not require a breach of fiduciary duty, or does it?", "start": 1598.024, "stop": 1604.456, "duration": 6.43, "cleanText": [["well", "e", "perhaps", "do", "not", "require", "a", "breach", "of", "fiduciary", "duty", "or", "do", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm sorry, which section?", "start": 1604.456, "stop": 1606.69, "duration": 2.23, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sorry", "which", "section"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "10(e), liability under... excuse me,--", "start": 1606.69, "stop": 1609.821, "duration": 3.13, "cleanText": [["e", "liability", "under", "excuse", "me"]]}, {"text": "--14.", "start": 1609.821, "stop": 1610.412, "duration": 0.59, "cleanText": [[]]}, {"text": "14(e).", "start": 1610.412, "stop": 1610.811, "duration": 0.4, "cleanText": [["e"]]}, {"text": "Does that require a breach of fiduciary duty?", "start": 1610.811, "stop": 1614.584, "duration": 3.77, "cleanText": [["do", "that", "require", "a", "breach", "of", "fiduciary", "duty"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "As the SEC has defined the acts that are prohibited in 14(e)3, it does not.", "start": 1614.584, "stop": 1620.548, "duration": 5.96, "cleanText": [["as", "the", "sec", "have", "define", "the", "act", "that", "be", "prohibit", "in", "e", "it", "do", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 1620.548, "stop": 1621.259, "duration": 0.71, "cleanText": [["right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "And I think that that is justified, Justice O'Connor, on two bases.", "start": 1621.259, "stop": 1624.602, "duration": 3.34, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "think", "that", "that", "be", "justified", "justice", "oconnor", "on", "two", "base"]]}, {"text": "First, Rule 14(e)3 in essence creates the duty to make disclosure, drawing on Congress' recognition that tender offers pose particular shareholder harms, and they pose particular dangers that the shareholders will not be able to make an important decision.", "start": 1624.602, "stop": 1640.914, "duration": 16.31, "cleanText": [["first", "rule", "e", "in", "essence", "create", "the", "duty", "to", "make", "disclosure", "draw", "on", "congress", "recognition", "that", "tender", "offer", "pose", "particular", "shareholder", "harm", "and", "they", "pose", "particular", "danger", "that", "the", "shareholder", "will", "not", "be", "able", "to", "make", "an", "important", "decision"]]}, {"text": "The SEC drew on the regulatory authority it was given to impose a duty to make disclosure, and second, the SEC's rule prevents violations that are akin to the misappropriation violation that occurs under section 10(b) by ensuring that when someone has material information of this character, they simply may not trade, even when there is no proof of a breach of fiduciary duty and deception in that.", "start": 1640.914, "stop": 1671.384, "duration": 30.47, "cleanText": [["the", "sec", "draw", "on", "the", "regulatory", "authority", "it", "be", "give", "to", "impose", "a", "duty", "to", "make", "disclosure", "and", "second", "the", "sec", "s", "rule", "prevents", "violation", "that", "be", "akin", "to", "the", "misappropriation", "violation", "that", "occur", "under", "section", "b", "by", "ensure", "that", "when", "someone", "have", "material", "information", "of", "this", "character", "they", "simply", "may", "not", "trade", "even", "when", "there", "be", "no", "proof", "of", "a", "breach", "of", "fiduciary", "duty", "and", "deception", "in", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sandra Day O'Connor", "textObjs": [{"text": "So that would extend liability to the thief?", "start": 1671.384, "stop": 1675.586, "duration": 4.2, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "would", "extend", "liability", "to", "the", "thief"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "It would extend liability to the thief so long as the thief acquired the information from the bidder or somebody acting on its behalf and knew that.", "start": 1675.586, "stop": 1684.231, "duration": 8.64, "cleanText": [["it", "would", "extend", "liability", "to", "the", "thief", "so", "long", "as", "the", "thief", "acquire", "the", "information", "from", "the", "bidder", "or", "somebody", "act", "on", "its", "behalf", "and", "know", "that"]]}, {"text": "Now, what is important about section 10(b)'s application to fraudulent conduct of this kind is that investors in the securities markets rely on the fact that the markets are essentially honest.", "start": 1684.231, "stop": 1697.991, "duration": 13.76, "cleanText": [["now", "what", "be", "important", "about", "section", "b", "s", "application", "to", "fraudulent", "conduct", "of", "this", "kind", "be", "that", "investor", "in", "the", "security", "market", "rely", "on", "the", "fact", "that", "the", "market", "be", "essentially", "honest"]]}, {"text": "No investor expects that he may have the skill, expertise, or analytical ability of everybody else in the market, and everyone who enters the market knows that they may be trading with somebody who's smarter than you are or better informed, and you're going to lose.", "start": 1697.991, "stop": 1711.249, "duration": 13.26, "cleanText": [["no", "investor", "expect", "that", "he", "may", "have", "the", "skill", "expertise", "or", "analytical", "ability", "of", "everybody", "else", "in", "the", "market", "and", "everyone", "who", "enter", "the", "market", "know", "that", "they", "may", "be", "trade", "with", "somebody", "who", "be", "smart", "than", "you", "be", "or", "good", "inform", "and", "you", "be", "go", "to", "lose"]]}, {"text": "But investors do assume that they are not trading with someone who acquired the informational advantage simply by fraud, simply by stealing information in breach of a fiduciary duty and using it for trading.", "start": 1711.249, "stop": 1723.488, "duration": 12.24, "cleanText": [["but", "investor", "do", "assume", "that", "they", "be", "not", "trade", "with", "someone", "who", "acquire", "the", "informational", "advantage", "simply", "by", "fraud", "simply", "by", "steal", "information", "in", "breach", "of", "a", "fiduciary", "duty", "and", "use", "it", "for", "trading"]]}, {"text": "That--", "start": 1723.488, "stop": 1724.309, "duration": 0.82, "cleanText": [["that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Dreeben, may I... you've come back to 10(b), and I had a question that I wanted to ask you and then I got distracted, and I'd like to pose it now.", "start": 1724.309, "stop": 1731.892, "duration": 7.58, "cleanText": [["mr", "dreeben", "may", "i", "you", "have", "come", "back", "to", "b", "and", "i", "have", "a", "question", "that", "i", "want", "to", "ask", "you", "and", "then", "i", "get", "distract", "and", "I", "have", "like", "to", "pose", "it", "now"]]}, {"text": "You made it clear, I think, that if the defendant in this case had simply disclosed his intention to use the information but did not receive authority, that there still would be a violation.", "start": 1731.892, "stop": 1746.432, "duration": 14.54, "cleanText": [["you", "make", "it", "clear", "i", "think", "that", "if", "the", "defendant", "in", "this", "case", "have", "simply", "disclose", "his", "intention", "to", "use", "the", "information", "but", "do", "not", "receive", "authority", "that", "there", "still", "would", "be", "a", "violation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No, I think that my position on that is that if there is disclosure to the client there would be no deception of the client.", "start": 1746.432, "stop": 1754.888, "duration": 8.46, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "think", "that", "my", "position", "on", "that", "be", "that", "if", "there", "be", "disclosure", "to", "the", "client", "there", "would", "be", "no", "deception", "of", "the", "client"]]}, {"text": "If there's disclosure to the firm, there would be no deception of the firm.", "start": 1754.888, "stop": 1758.27, "duration": 3.38, "cleanText": [["if", "there", "be", "disclosure", "to", "the", "firm", "there", "would", "be", "no", "deception", "of", "the", "firm"]]}, {"text": "There might be--", "start": 1758.27, "stop": 1759.051, "duration": 0.78, "cleanText": [["there", "might", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Okay.", "start": 1759.051, "stop": 1759.452, "duration": 0.4, "cleanText": [["okay"]]}, {"text": "That's the point at which I guess I got mixed up.", "start": 1759.452, "stop": 1760.831, "duration": 1.38, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "point", "at", "which", "i", "guess", "i", "get", "mixed", "up"]]}, {"text": "You've clarified it now.", "start": 1760.831, "stop": 1762.153, "duration": 1.32, "cleanText": [["you", "have", "clarify", "it", "now"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Okay.", "start": 1762.153, "stop": 1762.952, "duration": 0.8, "cleanText": [["okay"]]}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 1762.952, "stop": 1763.472, "duration": 0.52, "cleanText": [["thank", "you"]]}, {"text": "I would like to reserve the remainder of my time for rebuttal.", "start": 1763.472, "stop": 1765.996, "duration": 2.52, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "like", "to", "reserve", "the", "remainder", "of", "my", "time", "for", "rebuttal"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Very well, Mr. Dreeben.", "start": 1765.996, "stop": 1766.995, "duration": 1, "cleanText": [["very", "well", "mr", "dreeben"]]}, {"text": "Mr. French, we'll hear from you.", "start": 1766.995, "stop": 1769.118, "duration": 2.12, "cleanText": [["mr", "french", "we", "will", "hear", "from", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice, and may it please the Court:", "start": 1769.118, "stop": 1778.344, "duration": 9.23, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "and", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "The respondent in this case was a regular substantial investor in the stock market.", "start": 1778.344, "stop": 1785.549, "duration": 7.2, "cleanText": [["the", "respondent", "in", "this", "case", "be", "a", "regular", "substantial", "investor", "in", "the", "stock", "market"]]}, {"text": "He was convicted of 57 counts arising out of an alleged securities fraud and sentenced to 41 months in prison.", "start": 1785.549, "stop": 1795.806, "duration": 10.26, "cleanText": [["he", "be", "convict", "of", "count", "arise", "out", "of", "an", "alleged", "security", "fraud", "and", "sentence", "to", "month", "in", "prison"]]}, {"text": "The basis of that conviction was a set of legal theories that are not incorporated into the text of any statute, that have sown confusion among the courts, and that provide no guidance to participants in the stock market.", "start": 1795.806, "stop": 1814.148, "duration": 18.34, "cleanText": [["the", "basis", "of", "that", "conviction", "be", "a", "set", "of", "legal", "theory", "that", "be", "not", "incorporate", "into", "the", "text", "of", "any", "statute", "that", "have", "sow", "confusion", "among", "the", "court", "and", "that", "provide", "no", "guidance", "to", "participant", "in", "the", "stock", "market"]]}, {"text": "I ask the Court to consider briefly the application of the Government's theories to what are, for purposes of this appeal, the undisputed facts in this case.", "start": 1814.148, "stop": 1827.576, "duration": 13.43, "cleanText": [["i", "ask", "the", "court", "to", "consider", "briefly", "the", "application", "of", "the", "government", "s", "theory", "to", "what", "be", "for", "purpose", "of", "this", "appeal", "the", "undisputed", "fact", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "I am not now contesting facts.", "start": 1827.576, "stop": 1830.036, "duration": 2.46, "cleanText": [["i", "be", "not", "now", "contest", "fact"]]}, {"text": "I am asking the Court to think about the way the Government's theories apply to these facts.", "start": 1830.036, "stop": 1835.59, "duration": 5.55, "cleanText": [["i", "be", "ask", "the", "court", "to", "think", "about", "the", "way", "the", "government", "s", "theory", "apply", "to", "these", "fact"]]}, {"text": "On August 12, 1988, the Wall Street Journal reported that a British firm called Grand Metropolitan had put its hotel subsidiary, Intercontinental, up for auction to raise money for an acquisition.", "start": 1835.59, "stop": 1857.155, "duration": 21.57, "cleanText": [["on", "august", "the", "wall", "street", "journal", "report", "that", "a", "british", "firm", "call", "grand", "metropolitan", "have", "put", "its", "hotel", "subsidiary", "intercontinental", "up", "for", "auction", "to", "raise", "money", "for", "an", "acquisition"]]}, {"text": "On August 18, just 6 days later, a financial columnist named Dan Dorfman, announced on the Cable News Network that people close to Grand Metropolitan... and that is a common synonym in the trade for people inside Grand Metropolitan... are telling people in the street that Grand Metropolitan is interested in acquiring Pillsbury.", "start": 1857.155, "stop": 1884.233, "duration": 27.08, "cleanText": [["on", "august", "just", "day", "later", "a", "financial", "columnist", "name", "dan", "dorfman", "announce", "on", "the", "cable", "news", "network", "that", "people", "close", "to", "grand", "metropolitan", "and", "that", "be", "a", "common", "synonym", "in", "the", "trade", "for", "people", "inside", "grand", "metropolitan", "be", "tell", "people", "in", "the", "street", "that", "grand", "metropolitan", "be", "interested", "in", "acquire", "pillsbury"]]}, {"text": "Also on August 18, a broker called respondent to advise that he'd received a $9 million order to buy 250,000 shares of Pillsbury stock for a customer in London.", "start": 1884.233, "stop": 1901.355, "duration": 17.12, "cleanText": [["also", "on", "august", "a", "broker", "call", "respondent", "to", "advise", "that", "he", "have", "receive", "a", "million", "order", "to", "buy", "share", "of", "pillsbury", "stock", "for", "a", "customer", "in", "london"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. French, I gather you're trying to convince us that the doctrine would apply even if all the relevant information were in the public domain, and I'm assuming that we have a case that the jury found the relevant information was not in the public domain.", "start": 1901.355, "stop": 1916.704, "duration": 15.35, "cleanText": [["mr", "french", "i", "gather", "you", "be", "try", "to", "convince", "us", "that", "the", "doctrine", "would", "apply", "even", "if", "all", "the", "relevant", "information", "we", "be", "in", "the", "public", "domain", "and", "I", "be", "assume", "that", "we", "have", "a", "case", "that", "the", "jury", "find", "the", "relevant", "information", "be", "not", "in", "the", "public", "domain"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "What I'm suggesting is that if a theory can be applied to result in a conviction of Mr. O'Hagan on the basis of facts which very clearly in the record indicated that he placed all of his orders for Pillsbury options before August 26, and the Government only indicts him, as the prosecutor says, for trades made from August 26 on, then the theory is grotesque.", "start": 1916.704, "stop": 1950.725, "duration": 34.02, "cleanText": [["what", "I", "be", "suggest", "be", "that", "if", "a", "theory", "can", "be", "apply", "to", "result", "in", "a", "conviction", "of", "mr", "ohagan", "on", "the", "basis", "of", "fact", "which", "very", "clearly", "in", "the", "record", "indicate", "that", "he", "place", "all", "of", "his", "order", "for", "pillsbury", "option", "before", "august", "and", "the", "government", "only", "indict", "him", "as", "the", "prosecutor", "say", "for", "trade", "make", "from", "august", "on", "then", "the", "theory", "be", "grotesque"]]}, {"text": "You cannot, with--", "start": 1950.725, "stop": 1952.498, "duration": 1.77, "cleanText": [["you", "can", "not", "with"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "The reason it's grotesque, as I understand your presentation, is because the relevant information was in the public domain at the time he made his purchases.", "start": 1952.498, "stop": 1959.812, "duration": 7.31, "cleanText": [["the", "reason", "it", "be", "grotesque", "as", "i", "understand", "your", "presentation", "be", "because", "the", "relevant", "information", "be", "in", "the", "public", "domain", "at", "the", "time", "he", "make", "his", "purchase"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The relevant information was in the public domain and, as Your Honor knows, you may only be convicted, even under the Government's theory, if you trade on the basis of.", "start": 1959.812, "stop": 1973.84, "duration": 14.03, "cleanText": [["the", "relevant", "information", "be", "in", "the", "public", "domain", "and", "as", "your", "honor", "know", "you", "may", "only", "be", "convict", "even", "under", "the", "government", "s", "theory", "if", "you", "trade", "on", "the", "basis", "of"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right, but I would like to try and address the question of what we do with a case in which the facts are the way the Government presents them and the way presumably the jury thought they were, namely that your client acted entirely on the basis of inside information that was not in the public domain.", "start": 1973.84, "stop": 1989.801, "duration": 15.96, "cleanText": [["right", "but", "i", "would", "like", "to", "try", "and", "address", "the", "question", "of", "what", "we", "do", "with", "a", "case", "in", "which", "the", "fact", "be", "the", "way", "the", "government", "present", "them", "and", "the", "way", "presumably", "the", "jury", "think", "they", "we", "be", "namely", "that", "your", "client", "act", "entirely", "on", "the", "basis", "of", "inside", "information", "that", "be", "not", "in", "the", "public", "domain"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's--", "start": 1989.801, "stop": 1990.453, "duration": 0.65, "cleanText": [["that", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "And in that connection I'd be curious to know your view on whether, if it was... instead of your client, if it had been the partner who was in charge of the matter within the firm who had done this, would you say he would also be... would he be covered or not, in your view?", "start": 1990.453, "stop": 2004.41, "duration": 13.96, "cleanText": [["and", "in", "that", "connection", "I", "would", "be", "curious", "to", "know", "your", "view", "on", "whether", "if", "it", "be", "instead", "of", "your", "client", "if", "it", "have", "be", "the", "partner", "who", "be", "in", "charge", "of", "the", "matter", "within", "the", "firm", "who", "have", "do", "this", "would", "you", "say", "he", "would", "also", "be", "would", "he", "be", "cover", "or", "not", "in", "your", "view"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--In my view, we are dealing here with a statute that involves, as Mr. Dreeben said, disclosure.", "start": 2004.41, "stop": 2013.978, "duration": 9.57, "cleanText": [["in", "my", "view", "we", "be", "deal", "here", "with", "a", "statute", "that", "involve", "as", "mr", "dreeben", "say", "disclosure"]]}, {"text": "If Mr. O'Hagan had made... had had this private, nonpublic information that you're hypothesizing and disclosed to the Dorsey firm that he was going to trade on it, according to the Government's theory he couldn't have been prosecuted.", "start": 2013.978, "stop": 2029.906, "duration": 15.93, "cleanText": [["if", "mr", "ohagan", "have", "make", "have", "have", "this", "private", "nonpublic", "information", "that", "you", "be", "hypothesize", "and", "disclose", "to", "the", "dorsey", "firm", "that", "he", "be", "go", "to", "trade", "on", "it", "accord", "to", "the", "government", "s", "theory", "he", "could", "not", "have", "be", "prosecute"]]}, {"text": "To me, that seems to be preposterous.", "start": 2029.906, "stop": 2032.41, "duration": 2.5, "cleanText": [["to", "me", "that", "seem", "to", "be", "preposterous"]]}, {"text": "What's wrong with the Government's theory is, it doesn't have anything to do with unfair advantage being taken of a participant in the marketplace.", "start": 2032.41, "stop": 2042.736, "duration": 10.33, "cleanText": [["what", "be", "wrong", "with", "the", "government", "s", "theory", "be", "it", "do", "not", "have", "anything", "to", "do", "with", "unfair", "advantage", "be", "take", "of", "a", "participant", "in", "the", "marketplace"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I'm... my question is, what if he had been the partner in charge of the matter within the firm, and had acted entirely on the basis of nonpublic information.", "start": 2042.736, "stop": 2051.272, "duration": 8.54, "cleanText": [["well", "I", "be", "my", "question", "be", "what", "if", "he", "have", "be", "the", "partner", "in", "charge", "of", "the", "matter", "within", "the", "firm", "and", "have", "act", "entirely", "on", "the", "basis", "of", "nonpublic", "information"]]}, {"text": "Could the statute apply in that situation, in your view?", "start": 2051.272, "stop": 2054.393, "duration": 3.12, "cleanText": [["could", "the", "statute", "apply", "in", "that", "situation", "in", "your", "view"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "In my view, according to the Government's theory, the statute would apply.", "start": 2054.393, "stop": 2059.417, "duration": 5.02, "cleanText": [["in", "my", "view", "accord", "to", "the", "government", "s", "theory", "the", "statute", "would", "apply"]]}, {"text": "No.", "start": 2059.417, "stop": 2059.837, "duration": 0.42, "cleanText": [["no"]]}, {"text": "In my view, the statute cannot apply.", "start": 2059.837, "stop": 2061.82, "duration": 1.98, "cleanText": [["in", "my", "view", "the", "statute", "can", "not", "apply"]]}, {"text": "There has been no--", "start": 2061.82, "stop": 2063.29, "duration": 1.47, "cleanText": [["there", "have", "be", "no"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "Even if this man were the only lawyer working on the matter in the firm for the client.", "start": 2063.29, "stop": 2068.522, "duration": 5.23, "cleanText": [["even", "if", "this", "man", "we", "be", "the", "only", "lawyer", "work", "on", "the", "matter", "in", "the", "firm", "for", "the", "client"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--That's correct.", "start": 2068.522, "stop": 2069.864, "duration": 1.34, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "And had a clear duty to his client not to disclose.", "start": 2069.864, "stop": 2072.835, "duration": 2.97, "cleanText": [["and", "have", "a", "clear", "duty", "to", "his", "client", "not", "to", "disclose"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct, Justice Stevens.", "start": 2072.835, "stop": 2074.034, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "justice", "stevens"]]}, {"text": "In my view, it could not apply because--", "start": 2074.034, "stop": 2076.068, "duration": 2.03, "cleanText": [["in", "my", "view", "it", "could", "not", "apply", "because"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "But Mr. French, you would give a different answer, would you not, if the lawyer were in the firm that was assisting Pillsbury in this matter?", "start": 2076.068, "stop": 2085.803, "duration": 9.73, "cleanText": [["but", "mr", "french", "you", "would", "give", "a", "different", "answer", "would", "you", "not", "if", "the", "lawyer", "we", "be", "in", "the", "firm", "that", "be", "assist", "pillsbury", "in", "this", "matter"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I certainly would, Your Honor.", "start": 2085.803, "stop": 2087.235, "duration": 1.43, "cleanText": [["i", "certainly", "would", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "You have two lawyers, both with the same information, but one is working for the target company and the other is working for the potential takeover company, and you would distinguish those two cases.", "start": 2087.235, "stop": 2107.379, "duration": 20.14, "cleanText": [["you", "have", "two", "lawyer", "both", "with", "the", "same", "information", "but", "one", "be", "work", "for", "the", "target", "company", "and", "the", "other", "be", "work", "for", "the", "potential", "takeover", "company", "and", "you", "would", "distinguish", "those", "two", "case"]]}, {"text": "So everything that you said in the beginning, if we just made one change, made O'Hagan with the firm that's representing Pillsbury, there would be liability and you wouldn't contest that.", "start": 2107.379, "stop": 2120.007, "duration": 12.63, "cleanText": [["so", "everything", "that", "you", "say", "in", "the", "beginning", "if", "we", "just", "make", "one", "change", "make", "ohagan", "with", "the", "firm", "that", "be", "represent", "pillsbury", "there", "would", "be", "liability", "and", "you", "would", "not", "contest", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "I wouldn't be here today, Your Honor.", "start": 2120.007, "stop": 2121.726, "duration": 1.72, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "not", "be", "here", "today", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "The--", "start": 2121.726, "stop": 2122.608, "duration": 0.88, "cleanText": [["the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is--", "start": 2122.608, "stop": 2123.138, "duration": 0.53, "cleanText": [["be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The statute encompasses deception, and in the context of a nondisclosure, deception occurs in the presence of a fiduciary duty.", "start": 2123.138, "stop": 2134.226, "duration": 11.09, "cleanText": [["the", "statute", "encompass", "deception", "and", "in", "the", "context", "of", "a", "nondisclosure", "deception", "occurs", "in", "the", "presence", "of", "a", "fiduciary", "duty"]]}, {"text": "The lawyer inside Pillsbury has a fiduciary duty to the Pillsbury shareholders.", "start": 2134.226, "stop": 2140.49, "duration": 6.26, "cleanText": [["the", "lawyer", "inside", "pillsbury", "have", "a", "fiduciary", "duty", "to", "the", "pillsbury", "shareholder"]]}, {"text": "The lawyer outside Pillsbury does not have a fiduciary duty to the Pillsbury shareholders.", "start": 2140.49, "stop": 2145.944, "duration": 5.45, "cleanText": [["the", "lawyer", "outside", "pillsbury", "do", "not", "have", "a", "fiduciary", "duty", "to", "the", "pillsbury", "shareholder"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, are you basing your--", "start": 2145.944, "stop": 2146.815, "duration": 0.87, "cleanText": [["well", "be", "you", "base", "your"]]}, {"text": "--Deceive the sellers not just deceive somebody who's working for the... for... right?", "start": 2146.815, "stop": 2151.236, "duration": 4.42, "cleanText": [["deceive", "the", "seller", "not", "just", "deceive", "somebody", "who", "be", "work", "for", "the", "for", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 2151.236, "stop": 2152.218, "duration": 0.98, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "He has to have deceived the sellers in order--", "start": 2152.218, "stop": 2154.899, "duration": 2.68, "cleanText": [["he", "have", "to", "have", "deceive", "the", "seller", "in", "order"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's the basis for the distinction.", "start": 2154.899, "stop": 2156.829, "duration": 1.93, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "basis", "for", "the", "distinction"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--A deception in connection with the purchase or sale of a security is the basis of--", "start": 2156.829, "stop": 2161.243, "duration": 4.41, "cleanText": [["a", "deception", "in", "connection", "with", "the", "purchase", "or", "sale", "of", "a", "security", "be", "the", "basis", "of"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "But what you're focusing on is not the definition of fraud, not the definition of deception, but in connection with securities.", "start": 2161.243, "stop": 2167.909, "duration": 6.67, "cleanText": [["but", "what", "you", "be", "focus", "on", "be", "not", "the", "definition", "of", "fraud", "not", "the", "definition", "of", "deception", "but", "in", "connection", "with", "security"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I'm focusing on two things, Your Honor.", "start": 2167.909, "stop": 2172.461, "duration": 4.55, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "focus", "on", "two", "thing", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "First of all, I believe that what the Congress tried to adopt here was something to prevent securities fraud.", "start": 2172.461, "stop": 2180.356, "duration": 7.9, "cleanText": [["first", "of", "all", "i", "believe", "that", "what", "the", "congress", "try", "to", "adopt", "here", "be", "something", "to", "prevent", "security", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "I don't believe the Congress is attempting to regulate the relationships between lawyers and their firms, which are regulated by codes of professional responsibility, or husbands and wives, or fathers and sons, which is the context in which these misappropriation cases come up.", "start": 2180.356, "stop": 2197.778, "duration": 17.42, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "believe", "the", "congress", "be", "attempt", "to", "regulate", "the", "relationship", "between", "lawyer", "and", "their", "firm", "which", "be", "regulate", "by", "code", "of", "professional", "responsibility", "or", "husband", "and", "wife", "or", "father", "and", "son", "which", "be", "the", "context", "in", "which", "these", "misappropriation", "case", "come", "up"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, is it wrong for me to proceed through the statute and the relevant... and 10(b) 5 by asking first, is there fraud?", "start": 2197.778, "stop": 2204.661, "duration": 6.88, "cleanText": [["well", "be", "it", "wrong", "for", "me", "to", "proceed", "through", "the", "statute", "and", "the", "relevant", "and", "b", "by", "ask", "first", "be", "there", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "Second, is it in connection with the sale of securities?", "start": 2204.661, "stop": 2208.394, "duration": 3.73, "cleanText": [["second", "be", "it", "in", "connection", "with", "the", "sale", "of", "security"]]}, {"text": "And it seems to me that in the case that Justice Stevens put to you, where the principal partner working for Grand Met starts trading on the inside information, that there is fraud in the sense of deception.", "start": 2208.394, "stop": 2220.774, "duration": 12.38, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "that", "in", "the", "case", "that", "justice", "stevens", "put", "to", "you", "where", "the", "principal", "partner", "work", "for", "grand", "meet", "starts", "trading", "on", "the", "inside", "information", "that", "there", "be", "fraud", "in", "the", "sense", "of", "deception"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "It is possible--", "start": 2220.774, "stop": 2223.635, "duration": 2.86, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "possible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Now... now, maybe that's right, maybe that's wrong under your view, and I'd like to hear why.", "start": 2223.635, "stop": 2228.518, "duration": 4.88, "cleanText": [["now", "now", "maybe", "that", "be", "right", "maybe", "that", "be", "wrong", "under", "your", "view", "and", "I", "would", "like", "to", "hear", "why"]]}, {"text": "Now, I could understand if you went further and said there's not in connection with the sale of securities, but that's quite a different point.", "start": 2228.518, "stop": 2234.29, "duration": 5.77, "cleanText": [["now", "i", "could", "understand", "if", "you", "go", "further", "and", "say", "there", "be", "not", "in", "connection", "with", "the", "sale", "of", "security", "but", "that", "be", "quite", "a", "different", "point"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--There is not even deception there.", "start": 2234.29, "stop": 2239.105, "duration": 4.82, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "not", "even", "deception", "there"]]}, {"text": "There is theft, and contrary to Mr. Dreeben's position, theft of a piece of information is no different from theft of money.", "start": 2239.105, "stop": 2249.241, "duration": 10.14, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "theft", "and", "contrary", "to", "mr", "dreeben", "s", "position", "theft", "of", "a", "piece", "of", "information", "be", "no", "different", "from", "theft", "of", "money"]]}, {"text": "It's not fraud.", "start": 2249.241, "stop": 2251.492, "duration": 2.25, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "You can be prosecuted for the theft vis-a-vis yourself and the person from whom you stole, or the person from whom you stole may proceed against you to recover the money, but it's not deception.", "start": 2251.492, "stop": 2267.173, "duration": 15.68, "cleanText": [["you", "can", "be", "prosecute", "for", "the", "theft", "vis", "a", "vis", "yourself", "and", "the", "person", "from", "whom", "you", "steal", "or", "the", "person", "from", "whom", "you", "steal", "may", "proceed", "against", "you", "to", "recover", "the", "money", "but", "it", "be", "not", "deception"]]}, {"text": "Otherwise, every single theft would result in a prosecution for fraud, and that never happens.", "start": 2267.173, "stop": 2273.748, "duration": 6.58, "cleanText": [["otherwise", "every", "single", "theft", "would", "result", "in", "a", "prosecution", "for", "fraud", "and", "that", "never", "happen"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "What about the Carpenter case, Mr. French?", "start": 2273.748, "stop": 2276.639, "duration": 2.89, "cleanText": [["what", "about", "the", "carpenter", "case", "mr", "french"]]}, {"text": "What about the Carpenter case?", "start": 2276.639, "stop": 2280.452, "duration": 3.81, "cleanText": [["what", "about", "the", "carpenter", "case"]]}, {"text": "I mean, doesn't that suggest that theft can be brought within the securities statute?", "start": 2280.452, "stop": 2287.195, "duration": 6.74, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "do", "not", "that", "suggest", "that", "theft", "can", "be", "bring", "within", "the", "security", "statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "It suggests that theft can be brought within the mail fraud statute, Your Honor.", "start": 2287.195, "stop": 2292.54, "duration": 5.34, "cleanText": [["it", "suggest", "that", "theft", "can", "be", "bring", "within", "the", "mail", "fraud", "statute", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "As to the securities fraud statute, the Court was equally divided, and therefore I don't know what the Court thinks with respect to that issue.", "start": 2292.54, "stop": 2302.085, "duration": 9.55, "cleanText": [["as", "to", "the", "security", "fraud", "statute", "the", "court", "be", "equally", "divide", "and", "therefore", "i", "do", "not", "know", "what", "the", "court", "think", "with", "respect", "to", "that", "issue"]]}, {"text": "The Government cannot rely on Carpenter with respect to the mail fraud claim.", "start": 2302.085, "stop": 2307.588, "duration": 5.5, "cleanText": [["the", "government", "can", "not", "rely", "on", "carpenter", "with", "respect", "to", "the", "mail", "fraud", "claim"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is it possible that some of these difficult cases... you know, what you call the preposterous cases, the mothers, whatever it is... would be fairly dealt with through a requirement that a criminal conviction must be willful?", "start": 2307.588, "stop": 2321.548, "duration": 13.96, "cleanText": [["be", "it", "possible", "that", "some", "of", "these", "difficult", "case", "you", "know", "what", "you", "call", "the", "preposterous", "case", "the", "mother", "whatever", "it", "be", "would", "be", "fairly", "dealt", "with", "through", "a", "requirement", "that", "a", "criminal", "conviction", "must", "be", "willful"]]}, {"text": "I notice that word was in the criminal section, and does wilful mean that in this area, if you don't know the law, that's an excuse, so therefore in any of these borderline cases a defendant who didn't realize that what he was doing was against the securities law would be home free, and this would be reserved for the instances where people know that what they're doing is wrong as a matter of securities law.", "start": 2321.548, "stop": 2348.836, "duration": 27.29, "cleanText": [["i", "notice", "that", "word", "be", "in", "the", "criminal", "section", "and", "do", "wilful", "mean", "that", "in", "this", "area", "if", "you", "do", "not", "know", "the", "law", "that", "be", "an", "excuse", "so", "therefore", "in", "any", "of", "these", "borderline", "case", "a", "defendant", "who", "do", "not", "realize", "that", "what", "he", "be", "do", "be", "against", "the", "security", "law", "would", "be", "home", "free", "and", "this", "would", "be", "reserve", "for", "the", "instance", "where", "people", "know", "that", "what", "they", "be", "do", "be", "wrong", "as", "a", "matter", "of", "security", "law"]]}, {"text": "I'd like your reaction to that.", "start": 2348.836, "stop": 2350.408, "duration": 1.57, "cleanText": [["I", "would", "like", "your", "reaction", "to", "that"]]}, {"text": "I'm not certain whether that's correct or not.", "start": 2350.408, "stop": 2352.819, "duration": 2.41, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "not", "certain", "whether", "that", "be", "correct", "or", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Justice Breyer.", "start": 2352.819, "stop": 2353.971, "duration": 1.15, "cleanText": [["yes", "justice", "breyer"]]}, {"text": "I have several problems with it.", "start": 2353.971, "stop": 2358.061, "duration": 4.09, "cleanText": [["i", "have", "several", "problem", "with", "it"]]}, {"text": "One is that under the misappropriation theory no one will ever really know, because the misappropriation theory, even in the courts that have adopted it and follow it, is so confusing that the courts themselves... the court in Chestman, for example, says when you get outside the relationship with the shareholder, the... knowing whether or not the relationship applies is unclear.", "start": 2358.061, "stop": 2386.512, "duration": 28.45, "cleanText": [["one", "be", "that", "under", "the", "misappropriation", "theory", "no", "one", "will", "ever", "really", "know", "because", "the", "misappropriation", "theory", "even", "in", "the", "court", "that", "have", "adopt", "it", "and", "follow", "it", "be", "so", "confusing", "that", "the", "court", "themselves", "the", "court", "in", "chestman", "for", "example", "say", "when", "you", "get", "outside", "the", "relationship", "with", "the", "shareholder", "the", "know", "whether", "or", "not", "the", "relationship", "apply", "be", "unclear"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "But you see, that's the basis of my question.", "start": 2386.512, "stop": 2388.112, "duration": 1.6, "cleanText": [["but", "you", "see", "that", "be", "the", "basis", "of", "my", "question"]]}, {"text": "The defendant would be entitled to an instruction that if he didn't know that what he was doing was unlawful, he hasn't done it willfully.", "start": 2388.112, "stop": 2396.366, "duration": 8.25, "cleanText": [["the", "defendant", "would", "be", "entitle", "to", "an", "instruction", "that", "if", "he", "do", "not", "know", "that", "what", "he", "be", "do", "be", "unlawful", "he", "have", "not", "do", "it", "willfully"]]}, {"text": "I'm thinking of Ratzlaf.", "start": 2396.366, "stop": 2397.948, "duration": 1.58, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "think", "of", "ratzlaf"]]}, {"text": "I'm thinking of the cases that interpret willfully, and I wonder if that saves for the Government... saves them from your argument, because you're arguing this is all very unclear, and that's what I'd like a response to.", "start": 2397.948, "stop": 2410.515, "duration": 12.57, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "think", "of", "the", "case", "that", "interpret", "willfully", "and", "i", "wonder", "if", "that", "save", "for", "the", "government", "save", "them", "from", "your", "argument", "because", "you", "be", "argue", "this", "be", "all", "very", "unclear", "and", "that", "be", "what", "I", "would", "like", "a", "response", "to"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, it would be very helpful if that turned out to be, as the Government prosecutes these cases, the instruction.", "start": 2410.515, "stop": 2419.403, "duration": 8.89, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "would", "be", "very", "helpful", "if", "that", "turn", "out", "to", "be", "as", "the", "government", "prosecute", "these", "case", "the", "instruction"]]}, {"text": "There are several instructions in this case, as the record shows, against Mr. O'Hagan, that tell the jury that he doesn't have to know elements of the offense, for instance that he didn't have to know substantial steps were taken.", "start": 2419.403, "stop": 2431.142, "duration": 11.74, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "several", "instruction", "in", "this", "case", "as", "the", "record", "show", "against", "mr", "ohagan", "that", "tell", "the", "jury", "that", "he", "do", "not", "have", "to", "know", "element", "of", "the", "offense", "for", "instance", "that", "he", "do", "not", "have", "to", "know", "substantial", "step", "we", "be", "take"]]}, {"text": "But to me, it doesn't answer the question.", "start": 2431.142, "stop": 2433.632, "duration": 2.49, "cleanText": [["but", "to", "me", "it", "do", "not", "answer", "the", "question"]]}, {"text": "I believe, as Judge Luttig said in the Bryan case, this mode of analysis pulls apart a unitary concept.", "start": 2433.632, "stop": 2442.437, "duration": 8.8, "cleanText": [["i", "believe", "as", "judge", "luttig", "say", "in", "the", "bryan", "case", "this", "mode", "of", "analysis", "pull", "apart", "a", "unitary", "concept"]]}, {"text": "The unitary concept is deception or manipulation in connection with the purchase or sale of a security.", "start": 2442.437, "stop": 2451.324, "duration": 8.89, "cleanText": [["the", "unitary", "concept", "be", "deception", "or", "manipulation", "in", "connection", "with", "the", "purchase", "or", "sale", "of", "a", "security"]]}, {"text": "To me, that means the buyer or seller of the security deceives the person on the other side of the transaction.", "start": 2451.324, "stop": 2459.819, "duration": 8.49, "cleanText": [["to", "me", "that", "mean", "the", "buyer", "or", "seller", "of", "the", "security", "deceive", "the", "person", "on", "the", "other", "side", "of", "the", "transaction"]]}, {"text": "It's not as if you deceive someone over here and then later on you benefit from it by dealing with somebody else.", "start": 2459.819, "stop": 2467.253, "duration": 7.43, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "as", "if", "you", "deceive", "someone", "over", "here", "and", "then", "later", "on", "you", "benefit", "from", "it", "by", "deal", "with", "somebody", "else"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Dreeben's remark, it seems to me, fits with my theory of this case.", "start": 2467.253, "stop": 2474.609, "duration": 7.36, "cleanText": [["mr", "dreeben", "s", "remark", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "fit", "with", "my", "theory", "of", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "He says, there... it has to be in connection with the purchase or sale of a security because the only way Mr. O'Hagan could profit was in the purchase or sale of a security.", "start": 2474.609, "stop": 2486.016, "duration": 11.41, "cleanText": [["he", "say", "there", "it", "have", "to", "be", "in", "connection", "with", "the", "purchase", "or", "sale", "of", "a", "security", "because", "the", "only", "way", "mr", "ohagan", "could", "profit", "be", "in", "the", "purchase", "or", "sale", "of", "a", "security"]]}, {"text": "Not so.", "start": 2486.016, "stop": 2487.017, "duration": 1, "cleanText": [["not", "so"]]}, {"text": "That assumes Mr. O'Hagan has no imagination.", "start": 2487.017, "stop": 2489.859, "duration": 2.84, "cleanText": [["that", "assume", "mr", "ohagan", "have", "no", "imagination"]]}, {"text": "Mr. O'Hagan could have said, I now have a useful piece of information.", "start": 2489.859, "stop": 2494.712, "duration": 4.85, "cleanText": [["mr", "ohagan", "could", "have", "say", "i", "now", "have", "a", "useful", "piece", "of", "information"]]}, {"text": "I have misappropriated it.", "start": 2494.712, "stop": 2497.383, "duration": 2.67, "cleanText": [["i", "have", "misappropriate", "it"]]}, {"text": "I'm going to profit on it by selling it to the trade press.", "start": 2497.383, "stop": 2502.395, "duration": 5.01, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "go", "to", "profit", "on", "it", "by", "sell", "it", "to", "the", "trade", "press"]]}, {"text": "I can get a good fee for this information.", "start": 2502.395, "stop": 2504.987, "duration": 2.59, "cleanText": [["i", "can", "get", "a", "good", "fee", "for", "this", "information"]]}, {"text": "So the misappropriation would have occurred, but it had been disconnected from the purchase or sale of the security.", "start": 2504.987, "stop": 2513.963, "duration": 8.98, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "misappropriation", "would", "have", "occur", "but", "it", "have", "be", "disconnect", "from", "the", "purchase", "or", "sale", "of", "the", "security"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "It's not entirely disconnected.", "start": 2513.963, "stop": 2514.594, "duration": 0.63, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "entirely", "disconnect"]]}, {"text": "The trade press would only be interested in it because the people who read the trade press would be able to buy securities on the basis of this confidential information.", "start": 2514.594, "stop": 2522.828, "duration": 8.23, "cleanText": [["the", "trade", "press", "would", "only", "be", "interested", "in", "it", "because", "the", "people", "who", "read", "the", "trade", "press", "would", "be", "able", "to", "buy", "security", "on", "the", "basis", "of", "this", "confidential", "information"]]}, {"text": "I doubt if they would have--", "start": 2522.828, "stop": 2523.83, "duration": 1, "cleanText": [["i", "doubt", "if", "they", "would", "have"]]}, {"text": "--They would have just pushed it one step further back, but it still necessarily--", "start": 2523.83, "stop": 2527.102, "duration": 3.27, "cleanText": [["they", "would", "have", "just", "push", "it", "one", "step", "far", "back", "but", "it", "still", "necessarily"]]}, {"text": "--They wouldn't have paid this kind of price for it, either.", "start": 2527.102, "stop": 2527.763, "duration": 0.66, "cleanText": [["they", "would", "not", "have", "pay", "this", "kind", "of", "price", "for", "it", "either"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "All right.", "start": 2527.763, "stop": 2528.364, "duration": 0.6, "cleanText": [["all", "right"]]}, {"text": "I'll give you another hypothetical, Your Honor, because I'm firmly convinced that the statute doesn't read the way Mr. Dreeben says it does.", "start": 2528.364, "stop": 2535.149, "duration": 6.78, "cleanText": [["I", "will", "give", "you", "another", "hypothetical", "your", "honor", "because", "I", "be", "firmly", "convince", "that", "the", "statute", "do", "not", "read", "the", "way", "mr", "dreeben", "say", "it", "do"]]}, {"text": "You cannot disconnect the misappropriation from the purchase and sale of securities and say it's satisfied.", "start": 2535.149, "stop": 2540.973, "duration": 5.82, "cleanText": [["you", "can", "not", "disconnect", "the", "misappropriation", "from", "the", "purchase", "and", "sale", "of", "security", "and", "say", "it", "be", "satisfied"]]}, {"text": "Mr. O'Hagan's office in Minneapolis is across the street from the Pillsbury Company.", "start": 2540.973, "stop": 2546.086, "duration": 5.11, "cleanText": [["mr", "ohagan", "s", "office", "in", "minneapolis", "be", "across", "the", "street", "from", "the", "pillsbury", "company"]]}, {"text": "He could have said to himself, I have always wanted the business of the Pillsbury Company.", "start": 2546.086, "stop": 2551.409, "duration": 5.32, "cleanText": [["he", "could", "have", "say", "to", "himself", "i", "have", "always", "want", "the", "business", "of", "the", "pillsbury", "company"]]}, {"text": "I will walk across the street, misappropriating this information of my law firm and its client, deliver it to the Pillsbury Company, and suggest to the Pillsbury Company that in the future they might find it very desirable to use me for legal work.", "start": 2551.409, "stop": 2569.1, "duration": 17.69, "cleanText": [["i", "will", "walk", "across", "the", "street", "misappropriate", "this", "information", "of", "my", "law", "firm", "and", "its", "client", "deliver", "it", "to", "the", "pillsbury", "company", "and", "suggest", "to", "the", "pillsbury", "company", "that", "in", "the", "future", "they", "might", "find", "it", "very", "desirable", "to", "use", "me", "for", "legal", "work"]]}, {"text": "That wouldn't have had anything to do with the purchase and sale of the security, and yet it would have profited Mr. O'Hagan if it had worked.", "start": 2569.1, "stop": 2576.646, "duration": 7.55, "cleanText": [["that", "would", "not", "have", "have", "anything", "to", "do", "with", "the", "purchase", "and", "sale", "of", "the", "security", "and", "yet", "it", "would", "have", "profit", "mr", "ohagan", "if", "it", "have", "work"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, but all you're saying is, he could have done a lot of things that were not in connection with the sale of the security, but what he did it seems to me was in connection with the sale of the security.", "start": 2576.646, "stop": 2586.864, "duration": 10.22, "cleanText": [["yes", "but", "all", "you", "be", "say", "be", "he", "could", "have", "do", "a", "lot", "of", "thing", "that", "we", "be", "not", "in", "connection", "with", "the", "sale", "of", "the", "security", "but", "what", "he", "do", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "be", "in", "connection", "with", "the", "sale", "of", "the", "security"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "The cases of this Court have confined the statute to relationships between market participants.", "start": 2586.864, "stop": 2602.843, "duration": 15.98, "cleanText": [["the", "case", "of", "this", "court", "have", "confine", "the", "statute", "to", "relationship", "between", "market", "participant"]]}, {"text": "I admit not merely buyers and sellers.", "start": 2602.843, "stop": 2606.456, "duration": 3.61, "cleanText": [["i", "admit", "not", "merely", "buyer", "and", "seller"]]}, {"text": "They've included brokers.", "start": 2606.456, "stop": 2607.646, "duration": 1.19, "cleanText": [["they", "have", "include", "broker"]]}, {"text": "They've included other investors.", "start": 2607.646, "stop": 2609.688, "duration": 2.04, "cleanText": [["they", "have", "include", "other", "investor"]]}, {"text": "But at the time of the alleged fraud, neither Dorsey & Whitney nor Grand Met was a market participant.", "start": 2609.688, "stop": 2620.074, "duration": 10.39, "cleanText": [["but", "at", "the", "time", "of", "the", "allege", "fraud", "neither", "dorsey", "whitney", "nor", "grand", "met", "be", "a", "market", "participant"]]}, {"text": "Grand Met had a desire for a takeover.", "start": 2620.074, "stop": 2623.767, "duration": 3.69, "cleanText": [["grand", "meet", "have", "a", "desire", "for", "a", "takeover"]]}, {"text": "It had no money for the takeover.", "start": 2623.767, "stop": 2626.188, "duration": 2.42, "cleanText": [["it", "have", "no", "money", "for", "the", "takeover"]]}, {"text": "The transactions presumably ended by August 26.", "start": 2626.188, "stop": 2631.751, "duration": 5.56, "cleanText": [["the", "transaction", "presumably", "end", "by", "august"]]}, {"text": "Grand Met's own chief financial officer said that by September 18th they still didn't have the money.", "start": 2631.751, "stop": 2639.238, "duration": 7.49, "cleanText": [["grand", "meet", "s", "own", "chief", "financial", "officer", "say", "that", "by", "september", "th", "they", "still", "do", "not", "have", "the", "money"]]}, {"text": "They wanted to make a takeover.", "start": 2639.238, "stop": 2640.727, "duration": 1.49, "cleanText": [["they", "want", "to", "make", "a", "takeover"]]}, {"text": "They couldn't make a takeover.", "start": 2640.727, "stop": 2642.419, "duration": 1.69, "cleanText": [["they", "could", "not", "make", "a", "takeover"]]}, {"text": "It wasn't until October 4th that the takeover was proposed, was announced, so we have, I think for the very first time, a proposal by the Government that a fraud on a nonmarket participant be deemed to be in connection with the purchase and sale of securities.", "start": 2642.419, "stop": 2661.992, "duration": 19.57, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "until", "october", "th", "that", "the", "takeover", "be", "propose", "be", "announce", "so", "we", "have", "i", "think", "for", "the", "very", "first", "time", "a", "proposal", "by", "the", "government", "that", "a", "fraud", "on", "a", "nonmarket", "participant", "be", "deem", "to", "be", "in", "connection", "with", "the", "purchase", "and", "sale", "of", "security"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the rule is written that way.", "start": 2661.992, "stop": 2663.163, "duration": 1.17, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "rule", "be", "write", "that", "way"]]}, {"text": "The rule... I know you're going to bring me back to the statute, but just so far as the rule is concerned, the rule says it's unlawful to have a deceit or a fraud upon any person--", "start": 2663.163, "stop": 2673.708, "duration": 10.55, "cleanText": [["the", "rule", "i", "know", "you", "be", "go", "to", "bring", "me", "back", "to", "the", "statute", "but", "just", "so", "far", "as", "the", "rule", "be", "concern", "the", "rule", "say", "it", "be", "unlawful", "to", "have", "a", "deceit", "or", "a", "fraud", "upon", "any", "person"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 2673.708, "stop": 2674.219, "duration": 0.51, "cleanText": [["right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "--in connection with the purchase or sale of securities.", "start": 2674.219, "stop": 2676.361, "duration": 2.14, "cleanText": [["in", "connection", "with", "the", "purchase", "or", "sale", "of", "security"]]}, {"text": "It doesn't say upon a purchaser or seller of securities.", "start": 2676.361, "stop": 2679.062, "duration": 2.7, "cleanText": [["it", "do", "not", "say", "upon", "a", "purchaser", "or", "seller", "of", "security"]]}, {"text": "That's what it would say if your theory were to be adopted.", "start": 2679.062, "stop": 2684.566, "duration": 5.5, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "what", "it", "would", "say", "if", "your", "theory", "we", "be", "to", "be", "adopt"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "I agree it says any person, but it seems to me that rules are not allowed to stray outside the scope of their statute.", "start": 2684.566, "stop": 2691.31, "duration": 6.74, "cleanText": [["i", "agree", "it", "say", "any", "person", "but", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "that", "rule", "be", "not", "allow", "to", "stray", "outside", "the", "scope", "of", "their", "statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "Then we have to assume that Congress wouldn't intend... on your theory we could take the insiders, the most complete insiders of a corporation, say Grand Met if it were American, and they could go out and buy all the shares they wanted, knowing that those companies are about to be taken over.", "start": 2691.31, "stop": 2707.162, "duration": 15.85, "cleanText": [["then", "we", "have", "to", "assume", "that", "congress", "would", "not", "intend", "on", "your", "theory", "we", "could", "take", "the", "insider", "the", "most", "complete", "insider", "of", "a", "corporation", "say", "grand", "met", "if", "it", "we", "be", "american", "and", "they", "could", "go", "out", "and", "buy", "all", "the", "share", "they", "want", "know", "that", "those", "company", "be", "about", "to", "be", "take", "over"]]}, {"text": "They can buy the shares of the companies that are about to be taken over, and that would be lawful under the securities law, in your view.", "start": 2707.162, "stop": 2713.516, "duration": 6.35, "cleanText": [["they", "can", "buy", "the", "share", "of", "the", "company", "that", "be", "about", "to", "be", "take", "over", "and", "that", "would", "be", "lawful", "under", "the", "security", "law", "in", "your", "view"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "It would up until a point but there's a whole panoply of regulation relating to tender offers.", "start": 2713.516, "stop": 2719.858, "duration": 6.34, "cleanText": [["it", "would", "up", "until", "a", "point", "but", "there", "be", "a", "whole", "panoply", "of", "regulation", "relate", "to", "tender", "offer"]]}, {"text": "Once you've embarked on a tender offer you have to announce it, and there's restraints on how you can conduct it, and you cannot make misrepresentations in connection with it.", "start": 2719.858, "stop": 2731.937, "duration": 12.08, "cleanText": [["once", "you", "have", "embark", "on", "a", "tender", "offer", "you", "have", "to", "announce", "it", "and", "there", "have", "restraint", "on", "how", "you", "can", "conduct", "it", "and", "you", "can", "not", "make", "misrepresentation", "in", "connection", "with", "it"]]}, {"text": "I do not think this particular reading of this statute is necessary to keep tender offers clean.", "start": 2731.937, "stop": 2739.613, "duration": 7.68, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "this", "particular", "reading", "of", "this", "statute", "be", "necessary", "to", "keep", "tender", "offer", "clean"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. French, would you tell me, if your position is the one we adopt, what becomes of the 1988 legislation that provides... provided for a private right of action?", "start": 2739.613, "stop": 2754.342, "duration": 14.73, "cleanText": [["mr", "french", "would", "you", "tell", "me", "if", "your", "position", "be", "the", "one", "we", "adopt", "what", "become", "of", "the", "legislation", "that", "provide", "provide", "for", "a", "private", "right", "of", "action"]]}, {"text": "It appeared that Congress was operating on the basis of certain understandings about what 10(b) and 14(e) meant.", "start": 2754.342, "stop": 2763.499, "duration": 9.16, "cleanText": [["it", "appear", "that", "congress", "be", "operate", "on", "the", "basis", "of", "certain", "understanding", "about", "what", "b", "and", "e", "meant"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, Justice Ginsburg, two things about the 1988 legislation.", "start": 2763.499, "stop": 2771.073, "duration": 7.57, "cleanText": [["well", "justice", "ginsburg", "two", "thing", "about", "the", "legislation"]]}, {"text": "First, it was adopted... whatever they mean, it was adopted after my client's acts, and therefore it seems to me he can't have anticipated--", "start": 2771.073, "stop": 2779.999, "duration": 8.93, "cleanText": [["first", "it", "be", "adopt", "whatever", "they", "mean", "it", "be", "adopt", "after", "my", "client", "s", "act", "and", "therefore", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "he", "can", "not", "have", "anticipate"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, I don't mean with respect to your case, but you're asking us to make a ruling that will govern not simply this day and case--", "start": 2779.999, "stop": 2788.174, "duration": 8.18, "cleanText": [["oh", "i", "do", "not", "mean", "with", "respect", "to", "your", "case", "but", "you", "be", "ask", "us", "to", "make", "a", "ruling", "that", "will", "govern", "not", "simply", "this", "day", "and", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes.", "start": 2788.174, "stop": 2788.775, "duration": 0.6, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "--but that will interpret 10(b) and 14(e), and so I would like to know what becomes of that later legislation.", "start": 2788.775, "stop": 2796.749, "duration": 7.97, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "will", "interpret", "b", "and", "e", "and", "so", "i", "would", "like", "to", "know", "what", "become", "of", "that", "late", "legislation"]]}, {"text": "Is it in shambles?", "start": 2796.749, "stop": 2799.262, "duration": 2.51, "cleanText": [["be", "it", "in", "shamble"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think what I'd like the Court to do is think about all of the legislation and attempted legislation throughout the 1980's in thinking about that issue.", "start": 2799.262, "stop": 2811.93, "duration": 12.67, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "what", "I", "would", "like", "the", "court", "to", "do", "be", "think", "about", "all", "of", "the", "legislation", "and", "attempted", "legislation", "throughout", "the", "s", "in", "think", "about", "that", "issue"]]}, {"text": "In 1984, the SEC went to the Congress and proposed legislation that would have covered this subject matter, would have covered the misappropriation area, and then when Congress got ready to enact it said no, we would prefer vagueness and ambiguity.", "start": 2811.93, "stop": 2829.791, "duration": 17.86, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "sec", "go", "to", "the", "congress", "and", "propose", "legislation", "that", "would", "have", "cover", "this", "subject", "matter", "would", "have", "cover", "the", "misappropriation", "area", "and", "then", "when", "congress", "get", "ready", "to", "enact", "it", "say", "no", "we", "would", "prefer", "vagueness", "and", "ambiguity"]]}, {"text": "Please don't enact it.", "start": 2829.791, "stop": 2830.953, "duration": 1.16, "cleanText": [["please", "do", "not", "enact", "it"]]}, {"text": "Then in 1987, when the SEC went to the Congress with a proposal to enact the misappropriation theory, the Congress rejected it.", "start": 2830.953, "stop": 2840.66, "duration": 9.71, "cleanText": [["then", "in", "when", "the", "sec", "go", "to", "the", "congress", "with", "a", "proposal", "to", "enact", "the", "misappropriation", "theory", "the", "congress", "reject", "it"]]}, {"text": "Then in '88 it enacted something having to do with participants in the market that once again did not amend the language of 10(b)5, so it seems to me there is no basis for saying, as some of the amici have said, that the Congress has codified these theories into law.", "start": 2840.66, "stop": 2857.88, "duration": 17.22, "cleanText": [["then", "in", "it", "enact", "something", "have", "to", "do", "with", "participant", "in", "the", "market", "that", "once", "again", "do", "not", "amend", "the", "language", "of", "b", "so", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "there", "be", "no", "basis", "for", "say", "as", "some", "of", "the", "amici", "have", "say", "that", "the", "congress", "have", "codify", "these", "theory", "into", "law"]]}, {"text": "It has not enacted any of this into law.", "start": 2857.88, "stop": 2860.461, "duration": 2.58, "cleanText": [["it", "have", "not", "enact", "any", "of", "this", "into", "law"]]}, {"text": "So my answer is the 1984 legislation and the 1988 legislation have to be left to apply to 10b-5 as interpreted ultimately by this Court, and the Congress, if it wants to get the misappropriation theory into law, has to write it into law.", "start": 2860.461, "stop": 2879.743, "duration": 19.28, "cleanText": [["so", "my", "answer", "be", "the", "legislation", "and", "the", "legislation", "have", "to", "be", "leave", "to", "apply", "to", "b", "as", "interpret", "ultimately", "by", "this", "court", "and", "the", "congress", "if", "it", "want", "to", "get", "the", "misappropriation", "theory", "into", "law", "have", "to", "write", "it", "into", "law"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "So you disagree with what one of the amici briefs said, that... I think it was the one from the NASAA... stated that you virtually conceded that O'Hagan's conduct would have violated the 1988 act if it had post-dated that legislation.", "start": 2879.743, "stop": 2900.216, "duration": 20.47, "cleanText": [["so", "you", "disagree", "with", "what", "one", "of", "the", "amici", "brief", "say", "that", "i", "think", "it", "be", "the", "one", "from", "the", "nasaa", "state", "that", "you", "virtually", "concede", "that", "ohagan", "s", "conduct", "would", "have", "violate", "the", "act", "if", "it", "have", "post", "date", "that", "legislation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "I disagree, Your Honor.", "start": 2900.216, "stop": 2901.598, "duration": 1.38, "cleanText": [["i", "disagree", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "The amici briefs... one of the amicus briefs says the Congress codified the misappropriation theory.", "start": 2901.598, "stop": 2907.512, "duration": 5.91, "cleanText": [["the", "amici", "brief", "one", "of", "the", "amicus", "brief", "say", "the", "congress", "codify", "the", "misappropriation", "theory"]]}, {"text": "The Government says the Congress has validated the misappropriation theory.", "start": 2907.512, "stop": 2911.606, "duration": 4.09, "cleanText": [["the", "government", "say", "the", "congress", "have", "validate", "the", "misappropriation", "theory"]]}, {"text": "A third amicus brief says the Congress has not codified the misappropriation theory, but ratified it.", "start": 2911.606, "stop": 2918.101, "duration": 6.49, "cleanText": [["a", "third", "amicus", "brief", "say", "the", "congress", "have", "not", "codify", "the", "misappropriation", "theory", "but", "ratify", "it"]]}, {"text": "I don't know what ratified or validated means in these circumstances.", "start": 2918.101, "stop": 2923.554, "duration": 5.45, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "know", "what", "ratify", "or", "validated", "mean", "in", "these", "circumstance"]]}, {"text": "I know what enact means.", "start": 2923.554, "stop": 2925.256, "duration": 1.7, "cleanText": [["i", "know", "what", "enact", "mean"]]}, {"text": "Congress has not enacted it.", "start": 2925.256, "stop": 2926.597, "duration": 1.34, "cleanText": [["congress", "have", "not", "enact", "it"]]}, {"text": "So yes, I disagree.", "start": 2926.597, "stop": 2927.758, "duration": 1.16, "cleanText": [["so", "yes", "i", "disagree"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why hasn't Congress... what I'm actually thinking, Congress has... think of the case of the insider for the company itself, the company that's going to take over another company.", "start": 2927.758, "stop": 2939.225, "duration": 11.47, "cleanText": [["why", "have", "not", "congress", "what", "I", "be", "actually", "think", "congress", "have", "think", "of", "the", "case", "of", "the", "insider", "for", "the", "company", "itself", "the", "company", "that", "be", "go", "to", "take", "over", "another", "company"]]}, {"text": "Everybody knows that those insiders shouldn't go out and buy up stock in the takeover target secretly, and it deceives everybody in the company for which he works.", "start": 2939.225, "stop": 2951.954, "duration": 12.73, "cleanText": [["everybody", "know", "that", "those", "insider", "should", "not", "go", "out", "and", "buy", "up", "stock", "in", "the", "takeover", "target", "secretly", "and", "it", "deceive", "everybody", "in", "the", "company", "for", "which", "he", "work"]]}, {"text": "So the SEC, the expert organization, decides that that's so.", "start": 2951.954, "stop": 2956.436, "duration": 4.48, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "sec", "the", "expert", "organization", "decide", "that", "that", "be", "so"]]}, {"text": "It fits within the language of the statute.", "start": 2956.436, "stop": 2959.628, "duration": 3.19, "cleanText": [["it", "fit", "within", "the", "language", "of", "the", "statute"]]}, {"text": "And then of course you would be worried about criminal liability for vague theories, but that's where I came back to the word willfully.", "start": 2959.628, "stop": 2967.465, "duration": 7.84, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "of", "course", "you", "would", "be", "worry", "about", "criminal", "liability", "for", "vague", "theory", "but", "that", "be", "where", "i", "come", "back", "to", "the", "word", "willfully"]]}, {"text": "So I'm really asking this to see if there's anything more you want to say in that area.", "start": 2967.465, "stop": 2972.077, "duration": 4.61, "cleanText": [["so", "I", "be", "really", "ask", "this", "to", "see", "if", "there", "be", "anything", "more", "you", "want", "to", "say", "in", "that", "area"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'd be happy--", "start": 2972.077, "stop": 2972.968, "duration": 0.89, "cleanText": [["I", "would", "be", "happy"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "Should I see it as a delegation problem, an expert agency, literal language complied with, and criminal liability taken... unfair criminal liability taken care of by willfully?", "start": 2972.968, "stop": 2983.484, "duration": 10.52, "cleanText": [["should", "i", "see", "it", "as", "a", "delegation", "problem", "an", "expert", "agency", "literal", "language", "comply", "with", "and", "criminal", "liability", "take", "unfair", "criminal", "liability", "take", "care", "of", "by", "willfully"]]}, {"text": "I'm sketching that out for you so that I can get it--", "start": 2983.484, "stop": 2987.087, "duration": 3.6, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sketch", "that", "out", "for", "you", "so", "that", "i", "can", "get", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes, Justice Breyer.", "start": 2987.087, "stop": 2988.338, "duration": 1.25, "cleanText": [["yes", "justice", "breyer"]]}, {"text": "What we have is a... and I am not in a position to ask this Court to reverse several decades' worth of law, but what we have is a situation that's slipped its moorings.", "start": 2988.338, "stop": 2999.665, "duration": 11.33, "cleanText": [["what", "we", "have", "be", "a", "and", "i", "be", "not", "in", "a", "position", "to", "ask", "this", "court", "to", "reverse", "several", "decade", "worth", "of", "law", "but", "what", "we", "have", "be", "a", "situation", "that", "be", "slip", "its", "mooring"]]}, {"text": "Insider trading was supposed to be governed by section 16(b).", "start": 2999.665, "stop": 3003.427, "duration": 3.76, "cleanText": [["insider", "trading", "be", "suppose", "to", "be", "govern", "by", "section", "b"]]}, {"text": "Katie Roberts worked very hard to get insider trading under 10(b) more than 30 years after the statute was passed by saying it depends upon nondisclosure as between participants to a transaction.", "start": 3003.427, "stop": 3019.978, "duration": 16.55, "cleanText": [["katie", "robert", "work", "very", "hard", "to", "get", "insider", "trading", "under", "b", "more", "than", "year", "after", "the", "statute", "be", "pass", "by", "say", "it", "depend", "upon", "nondisclosure", "as", "between", "participant", "to", "a", "transaction"]]}, {"text": "This Court went along with that in Chiarella, but not further.", "start": 3019.978, "stop": 3025.561, "duration": 5.58, "cleanText": [["this", "court", "go", "along", "with", "that", "in", "chiarella", "but", "not", "far"]]}, {"text": "What the Congress needs, if it wants to get passed... and I can even conceptually do that.", "start": 3025.561, "stop": 3032.645, "duration": 7.08, "cleanText": [["what", "the", "congress", "need", "if", "it", "want", "to", "get", "pass", "and", "i", "can", "even", "conceptually", "do", "that"]]}, {"text": "I can... in my mind I can say, misrepresentation... deception can encompass nondisclosure when there is a duty to speak.", "start": 3032.645, "stop": 3041.952, "duration": 9.31, "cleanText": [["i", "can", "in", "my", "mind", "i", "can", "say", "misrepresentation", "deception", "can", "encompass", "nondisclosure", "when", "there", "be", "a", "duty", "to", "speak"]]}, {"text": "I can't get beyond that.", "start": 3041.952, "stop": 3043.794, "duration": 1.84, "cleanText": [["i", "can", "not", "get", "beyond", "that"]]}, {"text": "So if the Congress wants within the framework of 60 years of law to get beyond misrepresentation or nondisclosure constituting deception when there's a duty to speak, it should pass a statute about it, which it has not.", "start": 3043.794, "stop": 3062.046, "duration": 18.25, "cleanText": [["so", "if", "the", "congress", "want", "within", "the", "framework", "of", "year", "of", "law", "to", "get", "beyond", "misrepresentation", "or", "nondisclosure", "constitute", "deception", "when", "there", "be", "a", "duty", "to", "speak", "it", "should", "pass", "a", "statute", "about", "it", "which", "it", "have", "not"]]}, {"text": "Perhaps I should move to 14(e).", "start": 3062.046, "stop": 3069.781, "duration": 7.74, "cleanText": [["perhaps", "i", "should", "move", "to", "e"]]}, {"text": "It seems to me that there are two serious problems with 14(e) which I think the Government cannot deal with.", "start": 3069.781, "stop": 3079.996, "duration": 10.22, "cleanText": [["it", "seem", "to", "me", "that", "there", "be", "two", "serious", "problem", "with", "e", "which", "i", "think", "the", "government", "can", "not", "deal", "with"]]}, {"text": "One is the agency has not promulgated rules designed to help prevent frauds from arising.", "start": 3079.996, "stop": 3092.185, "duration": 12.19, "cleanText": [["one", "be", "the", "agency", "have", "not", "promulgate", "rule", "design", "to", "help", "prevent", "fraud", "from", "arise"]]}, {"text": "It simply redefined the word fraud.", "start": 3092.185, "stop": 3094.986, "duration": 2.8, "cleanText": [["it", "simply", "redefine", "the", "word", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "The statute prohibits fraudulent, deceptive, or manipulative acts.", "start": 3094.986, "stop": 3100.849, "duration": 5.86, "cleanText": [["the", "statute", "prohibit", "fraudulent", "deceptive", "or", "manipulative", "act"]]}, {"text": "The SEC announces that something is a fraudulent, deceptive, or manipulative act which doesn't have any element of fraud in it.", "start": 3100.849, "stop": 3111.538, "duration": 10.69, "cleanText": [["the", "sec", "announce", "that", "something", "be", "a", "fraudulent", "deceptive", "or", "manipulative", "act", "which", "do", "not", "have", "any", "element", "of", "fraud", "in", "it"]]}, {"text": "It just says you can't trade if you have the information.", "start": 3111.538, "stop": 3114.75, "duration": 3.21, "cleanText": [["it", "just", "say", "you", "can", "not", "trade", "if", "you", "have", "the", "information"]]}, {"text": "Again, if you look at one of the courts that's gone along with the rule, SEC v. Maio in the Seventh Circuit, says the rule requires a duty to disclose regardless of whether such information was obtained through a breach of fiduciary duty, so it seems to me that the rule has just outstripped the statute it's supposed to be implementing, and that's impermissible.", "start": 3114.75, "stop": 3140.476, "duration": 25.73, "cleanText": [["again", "if", "you", "look", "at", "one", "of", "the", "court", "that", "be", "go", "along", "with", "the", "rule", "sec", "v", "maio", "in", "the", "seventh", "circuit", "say", "the", "rule", "require", "a", "duty", "to", "disclose", "regardless", "of", "whether", "such", "information", "be", "obtain", "through", "a", "breach", "of", "fiduciary", "duty", "so", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "that", "the", "rule", "have", "just", "outstrip", "the", "statute", "it", "be", "suppose", "to", "be", "implement", "and", "that", "be", "impermissible"]]}, {"text": "The second thing wrong with the rule is, the rule says you mustn't trade in connection with a tender offer.", "start": 3140.476, "stop": 3147.8, "duration": 7.32, "cleanText": [["the", "second", "thing", "wrong", "with", "the", "rule", "be", "the", "rule", "say", "you", "must", "not", "trade", "in", "connection", "with", "a", "tender", "offer"]]}, {"text": "The SEC has said you may not trade if substantial steps have been taken toward a tender offer.", "start": 3147.8, "stop": 3155.667, "duration": 7.87, "cleanText": [["the", "sec", "have", "say", "you", "may", "not", "trade", "if", "substantial", "step", "have", "be", "take", "toward", "a", "tender", "offer"]]}, {"text": "That's not in the law.", "start": 3155.667, "stop": 3157.677, "duration": 2.01, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "not", "in", "the", "law"]]}, {"text": "That is an accretion to the law that's not there.", "start": 3157.677, "stop": 3160.359, "duration": 2.68, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "an", "accretion", "to", "the", "law", "that", "be", "not", "there"]]}, {"text": "It--", "start": 3160.359, "stop": 3161.51, "duration": 1.15, "cleanText": [["it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "--But their rulemaking authority under the law allows them to go beyond the law.", "start": 3161.51, "stop": 3166.654, "duration": 5.14, "cleanText": [["but", "their", "rulemaking", "authority", "under", "the", "law", "allow", "them", "to", "go", "beyond", "the", "law"]]}, {"text": "It allows them to make rules that will prevent a violation of the law.", "start": 3166.654, "stop": 3170.997, "duration": 4.34, "cleanText": [["it", "allow", "them", "to", "make", "rule", "that", "will", "prevent", "a", "violation", "of", "the", "law"]]}, {"text": "You concede that that allows them to make unlawful by rule some things that are not made unlawful by the statute, don't you?", "start": 3170.997, "stop": 3178.61, "duration": 7.61, "cleanText": [["you", "concede", "that", "that", "allow", "them", "to", "make", "unlawful", "by", "rule", "some", "thing", "that", "be", "not", "make", "unlawful", "by", "the", "statute", "do", "not", "you"]]}, {"text": "Or don't you?", "start": 3178.61, "stop": 3179.362, "duration": 0.75, "cleanText": [["or", "do", "not", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I do, but I don't concede that it authorizes them to change the criminal application of this statute.", "start": 3179.362, "stop": 3189.147, "duration": 9.78, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "but", "i", "do", "not", "concede", "that", "it", "authorize", "them", "to", "change", "the", "criminal", "application", "of", "this", "statute"]]}, {"text": "If the Court when it has an--", "start": 3189.147, "stop": 3193.722, "duration": 4.58, "cleanText": [["if", "the", "court", "when", "it", "have", "an"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John Paul Stevens", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't really understand your response.", "start": 3193.722, "stop": 3196.062, "duration": 2.34, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "really", "understand", "your", "response"]]}, {"text": "If it authorizes them to go beyond the law... you mean only for civil purposes?", "start": 3196.062, "stop": 3200.307, "duration": 4.24, "cleanText": [["if", "it", "authorize", "them", "to", "go", "beyond", "the", "law", "you", "mean", "only", "for", "civil", "purpose"]]}, {"text": "Is that what you're saying?", "start": 3200.307, "stop": 3201.516, "duration": 1.21, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "what", "you", "be", "say"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I'm... I'll say two things.", "start": 3201.516, "stop": 3203.959, "duration": 2.44, "cleanText": [["I", "be"], ["I", "will", "say", "two", "thing"]]}, {"text": "First, it plainly can't do it in the criminal context because it can't transform fraud into nonfraud and say, this is criminal, but beyond that, what I think it can do--", "start": 3203.959, "stop": 3216.565, "duration": 12.61, "cleanText": [["first", "it", "plainly", "can", "not", "do", "it", "in", "the", "criminal", "context", "because", "it", "can", "not", "transform", "fraud", "into", "nonfraud", "and", "say", "this", "be", "criminal", "but", "beyond", "that", "what", "i", "think", "it", "can", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Before you go beyond that, it's not transforming fraud into nonfraud.", "start": 3216.565, "stop": 3220.399, "duration": 3.83, "cleanText": [["before", "you", "go", "beyond", "that", "it", "be", "not", "transform", "fraud", "into", "nonfraud"]]}, {"text": "It's saying, this is nonfraud.", "start": 3220.399, "stop": 3221.938, "duration": 1.54, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "say", "this", "be", "nonfraud"]]}, {"text": "It's not covered by the statute, but we're prohibiting it nonetheless because the statute allows us to do it.", "start": 3221.938, "stop": 3228.414, "duration": 6.48, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "cover", "by", "the", "statute", "but", "we", "be", "prohibit", "it", "nonetheless", "because", "the", "statute", "allow", "us", "to", "do", "it"]]}, {"text": "It allows us to prohibit things in order to prevent fraud, not just to prohibit fraud but to prohibit other things in order to prevent fraud.", "start": 3228.414, "stop": 3237.19, "duration": 8.78, "cleanText": [["it", "allow", "us", "to", "prohibit", "thing", "in", "order", "to", "prevent", "fraud", "not", "just", "to", "prohibit", "fraud", "but", "to", "prohibit", "other", "thing", "in", "order", "to", "prevent", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "That's how the statute reads.", "start": 3237.19, "stop": 3239.28, "duration": 2.09, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "how", "the", "statute", "read"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No, Your Honor.", "start": 3239.28, "stop": 3243.033, "duration": 3.75, "cleanText": [["no", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "This redefines the word, fraud.", "start": 3243.033, "stop": 3246.506, "duration": 3.47, "cleanText": [["this", "redefine", "the", "word", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "It says, it shall be, it shall constitute fraudulent activity if you purchase after substantial steps have been taken.", "start": 3246.506, "stop": 3261.435, "duration": 14.93, "cleanText": [["it", "say", "it", "shall", "be", "it", "shall", "constitute", "fraudulent", "activity", "if", "you", "purchase", "after", "substantial", "step", "have", "be", "take"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's a different point you're making.", "start": 3261.435, "stop": 3263.346, "duration": 1.91, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "a", "different", "point", "you", "be", "make"]]}, {"text": "You are making the point that this rule might have been okay if it had read differently, if it had read, thou shalt not do this.", "start": 3263.346, "stop": 3272.472, "duration": 9.13, "cleanText": [["you", "be", "make", "the", "point", "that", "this", "rule", "might", "have", "be", "okay", "if", "it", "have", "read", "differently", "if", "it", "have", "read", "thou", "shalt", "not", "do", "this"]]}, {"text": "Instead, however, it reads doing this constitutes fraud under the... under 14(e), and that's simply false, so the rule is false.", "start": 3272.472, "stop": 3284.841, "duration": 12.37, "cleanText": [["instead", "however", "it", "read", "do", "this", "constitute", "fraud", "under", "the", "under", "e", "and", "that", "be", "simply", "false", "so", "the", "rule", "be", "false"]]}, {"text": "It's not that it--", "start": 3284.841, "stop": 3285.972, "duration": 1.13, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "that", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "The rule is false.", "start": 3285.972, "stop": 3286.393, "duration": 0.42, "cleanText": [["the", "rule", "be", "false"]]}, {"text": "The rule is--", "start": 3286.393, "stop": 3287.194, "duration": 0.8, "cleanText": [["the", "rule", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "--It's not that it does something that the Commission couldn't.", "start": 3287.194, "stop": 3288.904, "duration": 1.71, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "that", "it", "do", "something", "that", "the", "commission", "could", "not"]]}, {"text": "It does it in the wrong way.", "start": 3288.904, "stop": 3290.186, "duration": 1.28, "cleanText": [["it", "do", "it", "in", "the", "wrong", "way"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The rule is false.", "start": 3290.186, "stop": 3291.206, "duration": 1.02, "cleanText": [["the", "rule", "be", "false"]]}, {"text": "Moreover--", "start": 3291.206, "stop": 3292.448, "duration": 1.24, "cleanText": [["moreover"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "But could it have done it another way?", "start": 3292.448, "stop": 3294.859, "duration": 2.41, "cleanText": [["but", "could", "it", "have", "do", "it", "another", "way"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I don't think it could do... let me try to do this in conjunction.", "start": 3294.859, "stop": 3301.343, "duration": 6.48, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "it", "could", "do", "let", "me", "try", "to", "do", "this", "in", "conjunction"]]}, {"text": "I don't think it could do this in another way because there's no definition of substantial steps, and it is not possible for most participants in securities transactions to know that substantial steps have been taken.", "start": 3301.343, "stop": 3318.553, "duration": 17.21, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "it", "could", "do", "this", "in", "another", "way", "because", "there", "be", "no", "definition", "of", "substantial", "step", "and", "it", "be", "not", "possible", "for", "most", "participant", "in", "security", "transaction", "to", "know", "that", "substantial", "step", "have", "be", "take"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, but that's essentially a vagueness argument.", "start": 3318.553, "stop": 3322.367, "duration": 3.81, "cleanText": [["well", "but", "that", "be", "essentially", "a", "vagueness", "argument"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "It certainly is a vague--", "start": 3322.367, "stop": 3323.416, "duration": 1.05, "cleanText": [["it", "certainly", "be", "a", "vague"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "I suppose rather than a breach of delegated... or an excess of delegated authority.", "start": 3323.416, "stop": 3331.953, "duration": 8.54, "cleanText": [["i", "suppose", "rather", "than", "a", "breach", "of", "delegated", "or", "an", "excess", "of", "delegated", "authority"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--That's correct.", "start": 3331.953, "stop": 3333.424, "duration": 1.47, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "May I take an example in an area in which I practice heavily.", "start": 3333.424, "stop": 3338.356, "duration": 4.93, "cleanText": [["may", "i", "take", "an", "example", "in", "an", "area", "in", "which", "i", "practice", "heavily"]]}, {"text": "The Federal Trade Commission Act prohibits deceptive acts, unfair or deceptive acts or practices.", "start": 3338.356, "stop": 3346.332, "duration": 7.98, "cleanText": [["the", "federal", "trade", "commission", "act", "prohibit", "deceptive", "act", "unfair", "or", "deceptive", "act", "or", "practice"]]}, {"text": "In the context of that statute the agency, in prosecuting for deception, just takes straightforward misrepresentations, lots of different kinds but straightforward misrepresentations.", "start": 3346.332, "stop": 3359.63, "duration": 13.3, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "context", "of", "that", "statute", "the", "agency", "in", "prosecute", "for", "deception", "just", "take", "straightforward", "misrepresentation", "lot", "of", "different", "kind", "but", "straightforward", "misrepresentation"]]}, {"text": "In the concept of unfairness, it treads very carefully, conducts investigations, promulgates trade regulation rules, and then says we have identified a practice here that we deem to be unfair.", "start": 3359.63, "stop": 3375.141, "duration": 15.51, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "concept", "of", "unfairness", "it", "tread", "very", "carefully", "conduct", "investigation", "promulgates", "trade", "regulation", "rule", "and", "then", "say", "we", "have", "identify", "a", "practice", "here", "that", "we", "deem", "to", "be", "unfair"]]}, {"text": "We haven't amended the law to allow us to prohibit things that are fair.", "start": 3375.141, "stop": 3382.485, "duration": 7.34, "cleanText": [["we", "have", "not", "amend", "the", "law", "to", "allow", "us", "to", "prohibit", "thing", "that", "be", "fair"]]}, {"text": "We've identified this act as unfair.", "start": 3382.485, "stop": 3385.617, "duration": 3.13, "cleanText": [["we", "have", "identify", "this", "act", "as", "unfair"]]}, {"text": "And then it goes forward on a very careful basis with prosecutions that only lead to injunctive results.", "start": 3385.617, "stop": 3392.121, "duration": 6.5, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "it", "go", "forward", "on", "a", "very", "careful", "basis", "with", "prosecution", "that", "only", "lead", "to", "injunctive", "result"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "But that basically is then kind of an administrative process argument, and once again it seems to me you're not saying when you make that argument that they have exceeded their... that the essential problem is that they have exceeded their delegated authority, but the contrast that you are drawing is that they were more careful about predicating their exercise of delegated authority.", "start": 3392.121, "stop": 3415.147, "duration": 23.03, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "basically", "be", "then", "kind", "of", "an", "administrative", "process", "argument", "and", "once", "again", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "you", "be", "not", "say", "when", "you", "make", "that", "argument", "that", "they", "have", "exceed", "their", "that", "the", "essential", "problem", "be", "that", "they", "have", "exceed", "their", "delegated", "authority", "but", "the", "contrast", "that", "you", "be", "draw", "be", "that", "they", "we", "be", "more", "careful", "about", "predicate", "their", "exercise", "of", "delegated", "authority"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "And they certainly have been more careful.", "start": 3415.147, "stop": 3419.591, "duration": 4.44, "cleanText": [["and", "they", "certainly", "have", "be", "more", "careful"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "But if that's the nub of what you're arguing, it's not that they've exceeded the authority in our case, if that's the point of your argument, but that they just didn't go about it the right way.", "start": 3419.591, "stop": 3428.947, "duration": 9.36, "cleanText": [["but", "if", "that", "be", "the", "nub", "of", "what", "you", "be", "argue", "it", "be", "not", "that", "they", "have", "exceed", "the", "authority", "in", "our", "case", "if", "that", "be", "the", "point", "of", "your", "argument", "but", "that", "they", "just", "do", "not", "go", "about", "it", "the", "right", "way"]]}, {"text": "Their process was defective.", "start": 3428.947, "stop": 3430.827, "duration": 1.88, "cleanText": [["their", "process", "be", "defective"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, I really am going beyond that.", "start": 3430.827, "stop": 3433.318, "duration": 2.49, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "really", "be", "go", "beyond", "that"]]}, {"text": "I am--", "start": 3433.318, "stop": 3433.728, "duration": 0.41, "cleanText": [["i", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "David H. Souter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Okay, then I don't--", "start": 3433.728, "stop": 3434.59, "duration": 0.86, "cleanText": [["okay", "then", "i", "do", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I am saying... I am saying that when the statute says you must not commit fraud in connection with a tender offer, the agency cannot say, you are also subject to prosecution when... even when you don't commit fraud, and even when no tender offer has been launched, but because substantial steps have been taken.", "start": 3434.59, "stop": 3458.957, "duration": 24.37, "cleanText": [["i", "be", "say", "i", "be", "say", "that", "when", "the", "statute", "say", "you", "must", "not", "commit", "fraud", "in", "connection", "with", "a", "tender", "offer", "the", "agency", "can", "not", "say", "you", "be", "also", "subject", "to", "prosecution", "when", "even", "when", "you", "do", "not", "commit", "fraud", "and", "even", "when", "no", "tender", "offer", "have", "be", "launch", "but", "because", "substantial", "step", "have", "be", "take"]]}, {"text": "That rewrites the law.", "start": 3458.957, "stop": 3460.577, "duration": 1.62, "cleanText": [["that", "rewrite", "the", "law"]]}, {"text": "That is not a rule that implements the law.", "start": 3460.577, "stop": 3462.838, "duration": 2.26, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "not", "a", "rule", "that", "implement", "the", "law"]]}, {"text": "It rewrites the law, and that's the distinction I'm drawing.", "start": 3462.838, "stop": 3465.7, "duration": 2.86, "cleanText": [["it", "rewrite", "the", "law", "and", "that", "be", "the", "distinction", "I", "be", "draw"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Mr. French, does the Federal Trade Commission Act say that the Federal Trade Commission shall, by rules and regulations, define and prescribe means reasonably designed to prevent unfair or deceptive trade practices.", "start": 3465.7, "stop": 3481.781, "duration": 16.08, "cleanText": [["mr", "french", "do", "the", "federal", "trade", "commission", "act", "say", "that", "the", "federal", "trade", "commission", "shall", "by", "rule", "and", "regulation", "define", "and", "prescribe", "mean", "reasonably", "design", "to", "prevent", "unfair", "or", "deceptive", "trade", "practice"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't recall the language producing the implementation.", "start": 3481.781, "stop": 3485.473, "duration": 3.69, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "recall", "the", "language", "produce", "the", "implementation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't think it does.", "start": 3485.473, "stop": 3485.834, "duration": 0.36, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "it", "do"]]}, {"text": "That's the crucial sentence here which allows this agency, as I think the Federal Trade Commission Act does not allow the Federal Trade Commission to go beyond what the statute says and to define other things as unlawful in order to prevent the things that the statute prohibits.", "start": 3485.834, "stop": 3502.014, "duration": 16.18, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "crucial", "sentence", "here", "which", "allow", "this", "agency", "as", "i", "think", "the", "federal", "trade", "commission", "act", "do", "not", "allow", "the", "federal", "trade", "commission", "to", "go", "beyond", "what", "the", "statute", "say", "and", "to", "define", "other", "thing", "as", "unlawful", "in", "order", "to", "prevent", "the", "thing", "that", "the", "statute", "prohibits"]]}, {"text": "I think that's the fair meaning of that sentence, now.", "start": 3502.014, "stop": 3504.506, "duration": 2.49, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "be", "the", "fair", "meaning", "of", "that", "sentence", "now"]]}, {"text": "Maybe you say that's an unconstitutional delegation or something, but it seems to me you have to grapple with the reality that Congress has told this agency, you can make unlawful things that the statute does not make unlawful.", "start": 3504.506, "stop": 3516.503, "duration": 12, "cleanText": [["maybe", "you", "say", "that", "be", "an", "unconstitutional", "delegation", "or", "something", "but", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "you", "have", "to", "grapple", "with", "the", "reality", "that", "congress", "have", "tell", "this", "agency", "you", "can", "make", "unlawful", "thing", "that", "the", "statute", "do", "not", "make", "unlawful"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "You can put into a class of prohibited conduct in some way or another things that you define as reasonably designed to prevent fraudulent acts.", "start": 3516.503, "stop": 3533.025, "duration": 16.52, "cleanText": [["you", "can", "put", "into", "a", "class", "of", "prohibited", "conduct", "in", "some", "way", "or", "another", "thing", "that", "you", "define", "as", "reasonably", "design", "to", "prevent", "fraudulent", "act"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "And suppose you go on and say, and we will treat these as if they were fraudulent acts?", "start": 3533.025, "stop": 3537.707, "duration": 4.68, "cleanText": [["and", "suppose", "you", "go", "on", "and", "say", "and", "we", "will", "treat", "these", "as", "if", "they", "we", "be", "fraudulent", "act"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "I do not believe you can go on and say, you may treat... we will treat these as fraudulent acts.", "start": 3537.707, "stop": 3543.461, "duration": 5.75, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "believe", "you", "can", "go", "on", "and", "say", "you", "may", "treat", "we", "will", "treat", "these", "as", "fraudulent", "act"]]}, {"text": "There has to be for people to be not at risk all the times--", "start": 3543.461, "stop": 3548.693, "duration": 5.23, "cleanText": [["there", "have", "to", "be", "for", "people", "to", "be", "not", "at", "risk", "all", "the", "time"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well but the sanction is the same.", "start": 3548.693, "stop": 3550.774, "duration": 2.08, "cleanText": [["well", "but", "the", "sanction", "be", "the", "same"]]}, {"text": "It just says that the sanction mechanisms of the statute are employed.", "start": 3550.774, "stop": 3556.708, "duration": 5.93, "cleanText": [["it", "just", "say", "that", "the", "sanction", "mechanism", "of", "the", "statute", "be", "employ"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--You may not, Your Honor, I think, put people at risk of prosecution for fraudulent acts committed in connection with a tender offer by announcing that nonfraudulent acts are fraudulent acts and can be prosecuted when there isn't any--", "start": 3556.708, "stop": 3576.423, "duration": 19.71, "cleanText": [["you", "may", "not", "your", "honor", "i", "think", "put", "people", "at", "risk", "of", "prosecution", "for", "fraudulent", "act", "commit", "in", "connection", "with", "a", "tender", "offer", "by", "announce", "that", "nonfraudulent", "act", "be", "fraudulent", "act", "and", "can", "be", "prosecute", "when", "there", "be", "not", "any"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, there has to be the premise that they're necessary to avoid other fraudulent acts.", "start": 3576.423, "stop": 3581.476, "duration": 5.05, "cleanText": [["well", "there", "have", "to", "be", "the", "premise", "that", "they", "be", "necessary", "to", "avoid", "other", "fraudulent", "act"]]}, {"text": "Of course, the text says fraudulent, deceptive, or manipulative.", "start": 3581.476, "stop": 3585.91, "duration": 4.43, "cleanText": [["of", "course", "the", "text", "say", "fraudulent", "deceptive", "or", "manipulative"]]}, {"text": "It's kind of a broad term.", "start": 3585.91, "stop": 3587.2, "duration": 1.29, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "kind", "of", "a", "broad", "term"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--It certainly is, but I believe the Court in Schreiber has equated deceptive and manipulative under this statute with deceptive and manipulative under 10(b), so it has some content that narrows somewhat the breadth of it.", "start": 3587.2, "stop": 3604.861, "duration": 17.66, "cleanText": [["it", "certainly", "be", "but", "i", "believe", "the", "court", "in", "schreiber", "have", "equate", "deceptive", "and", "manipulative", "under", "this", "statute", "with", "deceptive", "and", "manipulative", "under", "b", "so", "it", "have", "some", "content", "that", "narrow", "somewhat", "the", "breadth", "of", "it"]]}, {"text": "I don't know if the Court wishes me to speak on the subject of mail fraud.", "start": 3604.861, "stop": 3610.304, "duration": 5.44, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "know", "if", "the", "court", "wish", "me", "to", "speak", "on", "the", "subject", "of", "mail", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Dreeben did not, and I'm willing to leave it to the briefs.", "start": 3610.304, "stop": 3614.207, "duration": 3.9, "cleanText": [["mr", "dreeben", "do", "not", "and", "I", "be", "willing", "to", "leave", "it", "to", "the", "brief"]]}, {"text": "I would say with respect to that that all that happened here is that in the Eighth Circuit, the Eighth Circuit--", "start": 3614.207, "stop": 3620.502, "duration": 6.3, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "say", "with", "respect", "to", "that", "that", "all", "that", "happen", "here", "be", "that", "in", "the", "eighth", "circuit", "the", "eighth", "circuit"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. French, your time has expired.", "start": 3620.502, "stop": 3623.744, "duration": 3.24, "cleanText": [["mr", "french", "your", "time", "have", "expire"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "John D. French", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Thank you, Mr. Chief Justice.", "start": 3623.744, "stop": 3624.903, "duration": 1.16, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "mr", "chief", "justice"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Dreeben, you have a little over a minute left.", "start": 3624.903, "stop": 3627.575, "duration": 2.67, "cleanText": [["mr", "dreeben", "you", "have", "a", "little", "over", "a", "minute", "left"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, Mr. Chief Justice.", "start": 3627.575, "stop": 3630.416, "duration": 2.84, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "mr", "chief", "justice"]]}, {"text": "In order to convict respondent on the section 10(b) count, the jury had to find that he acted with the intent to deceive, manipulate, or deprive... these are in the jury instructions at page 199 of the joint appendix... and the statutory requirement for the imposition of imprisonment requires that he be shown to have knowledge of the regulation or rule that he violated.", "start": 3630.416, "stop": 3657.355, "duration": 26.94, "cleanText": [["in", "order", "to", "convict", "respondent", "on", "the", "section", "b", "count", "the", "jury", "have", "to", "find", "that", "he", "act", "with", "the", "intent", "to", "deceive", "manipulate", "or", "deprive", "these", "be", "in", "the", "jury", "instruction", "at", "page", "of", "the", "joint", "appendix", "and", "the", "statutory", "requirement", "for", "the", "imposition", "of", "imprisonment", "require", "that", "he", "be", "show", "to", "have", "knowledge", "of", "the", "regulation", "or", "rule", "that", "he", "violate"]]}, {"text": "He cannot show that... if he shows that he did not have knowledge of it, he cannot be imprisoned, but the statute does require proof of wilfulness in order to sustain any criminal conviction.", "start": 3657.355, "stop": 3668.003, "duration": 10.65, "cleanText": [["he", "can", "not", "show", "that", "if", "he", "show", "that", "he", "do", "not", "have", "knowledge", "of", "it", "he", "can", "not", "be", "imprison", "but", "the", "statute", "do", "require", "proof", "of", "wilfulness", "in", "order", "to", "sustain", "any", "criminal", "conviction"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Dreeben, I hate to use up any of your short time, but there's a new point which came out in oral argument here which I don't recall in the briefs, and I want to know what your response to it is, and that is, assuming that 14(e), as I think is true, does allow this agency to make unlawful things that the statute itself does not, has it purported to do that in its regulation?", "start": 3668.003, "stop": 3691.147, "duration": 23.14, "cleanText": [["mr", "dreeben", "i", "hate", "to", "use", "up", "any", "of", "your", "short", "time", "but", "there", "be", "a", "new", "point", "which", "come", "out", "in", "oral", "argument", "here", "which", "i", "do", "not", "recall", "in", "the", "brief", "and", "i", "want", "to", "know", "what", "your", "response", "to", "it", "be", "and", "that", "be", "assume", "that", "e", "as", "i", "think", "be", "true", "do", "allow", "this", "agency", "to", "make", "unlawful", "thing", "that", "the", "statute", "itself", "do", "not", "have", "it", "purport", "to", "do", "that", "in", "its", "regulation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "Justice Scalia--", "start": 3691.147, "stop": 3692.459, "duration": 1.31, "cleanText": [["justice", "scalia"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "And if it has not purported to do that, has not purported by that regulation to prescribe means reasonably designed, but rather in its regulation simply redefines what constitutes fraud or deception, then is that an exercise of the power that's given by that second sentence of 14(e)?", "start": 3692.459, "stop": 3714.642, "duration": 22.18, "cleanText": [["and", "if", "it", "have", "not", "purport", "to", "do", "that", "have", "not", "purport", "by", "that", "regulation", "to", "prescribe", "mean", "reasonably", "design", "but", "rather", "in", "its", "regulation", "simply", "redefine", "what", "constitute", "fraud", "or", "deception", "then", "be", "that", "an", "exercise", "of", "the", "power", "that", "be", "give", "by", "that", "second", "sentence", "of", "e"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I think that it is, Justice Scalia.", "start": 3714.642, "stop": 3716.152, "duration": 1.51, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "it", "be", "justice", "scalia"]]}, {"text": "The ultimate... may I answer?", "start": 3716.152, "stop": 3718.375, "duration": 2.22, "cleanText": [["the", "ultimate", "may", "i", "answer"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 3718.375, "stop": 3718.976, "duration": 0.6, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Michael R. Dreeben", "textObjs": [{"text": "The ultimate question is whether the SEC's prohibition on trading, which is clearly described in the rule, is within its statutory authority which is a question for the court, and the court may determine that the SEC's prohibition does satisfy the statute based on either the defining prong or the means reasonably designed to prevent, and it's analysis of the reasons that are given.", "start": 3718.976, "stop": 3743.932, "duration": 24.96, "cleanText": [["the", "ultimate", "question", "be", "whether", "the", "sec", "s", "prohibition", "on", "trading", "which", "be", "clearly", "describe", "in", "the", "rule", "be", "within", "its", "statutory", "authority", "which", "be", "a", "question", "for", "the", "court", "and", "the", "court", "may", "determine", "that", "the", "sec", "s", "prohibition", "do", "satisfy", "the", "statute", "base", "on", "either", "the", "defining", "prong", "or", "the", "mean", "reasonably", "design", "to", "prevent", "and", "it", "be", "analysis", "of", "the", "reason", "that", "be", "give"]]}, {"text": "We address this question in our brief in opposition in the Chestman case.", "start": 3743.932, "stop": 3747.675, "duration": 3.74, "cleanText": [["we", "address", "this", "question", "in", "our", "brief", "in", "opposition", "in", "the", "chestman", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William H. Rehnquist", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, Mr. Dreeben.", "start": 3747.675, "stop": 3748.606, "duration": 0.93, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "mr", "dreeben"]]}, {"text": "I think you've answered the question.", "start": 3748.606, "stop": 3750.258, "duration": 1.65, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "you", "have", "answer", "the", "question"]]}, {"text": "The case is submitted.", "start": 3750.258, "stop": 3751.34, "duration": 1.08, "cleanText": [["the", "case", "be", "submit"]]}]}]}], "decidedBy": "Rehnquist Court", "arguedOn": "Apr 16, 1997", "petitioner": "United States", "respondent": "O'Hagan", "docket": "96-842", "citation": "521US642(1997)", "justiaLink": "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/521/642", "lowerCourt": "United States Court of Appeals for the Eighth Circuit", "grantedOn": "", "decidedOn": "Jun 25, 1997", "wikiData": {"title": "United States v. O'Hagan", "Litigants": "United States v. O'Hagan", "ArgueDate": "April 16", "ArgueYear": "1997", "DecideDate": "June 25", "DecideYear": "1997", "FullName": "United States, Petitioner v. James Herman O'Hagan", "USVol": "521", "USPage": "642", "ParallelCitations": "117 S. Ct. 2199; 138 [[L. Ed. 2d]] 724", "Prior": "92 [[F.3d]] [https://law.justia.com/cases/federal/appellate-courts/F3/92/612/517399/ 612] ([[8th Cir.]] 1996); [[Certiorari|cert]]. granted, {{ussc|519|1087|1997|el=no}}.", "Subsequent": "On remand, 139 [[F.3d]] [https://law.justia.com/cases/federal/appellate-courts/F3/139/641/588664/ 641] (8th Cir. 1998).", "Holding": "A person who trades in securities for personal profit, using confidential information misappropriated in breach of a fiduciary duty to the source of the information, may be held liable for violating  10(b) and Rule 10b-5, and so the SEC did not exceed its authority under  14(e) by adopting Rule 14e-3(a) without requiring a showing that such trading entailed a breach of fiduciary duty.", "SCOTUS": "19942005", "Majority": "Ginsburg", "JoinMajority": "Stevens, O'Connor, Kennedy, Souter, Breyer; Scalia (parts I, III, IV)", "Concurrence/Dissent": "Scalia", "Concurrence/Dissent2": "Thomas", "JoinConcurrence/Dissent2": "Rehnquist", "LawsApplied": "[[Securities Exchange Act of 1934|Securities Exchange Act of 1934  10(b)]], [[Rule 10b-5]]"}}